title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, using pineapple juice for liquid.
Add water to make amount required.
Bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven, using a well-greased and floured 15 x 10 1/2 x 1 pan.
Cool in pan.
Blend together with beater the cream cheese, instant pudding and milk.
Fold in drained pineapple. Spread over top of cooled cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cut up chicken.
Cook rice in broth or water.
Mix onion soup, creamed soup and 1/2 cup milk with rice.
Butter a casserole dish and place rice mixture in dish.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: italian pasta cookie(biscotta di pasta)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until
fluffy.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill dough for 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Shape in 1-inch
log shapes and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until
lightly
golden,
approximately
12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies
are
still
warm,
sift heavily with powdered
sugar. Cool
completely
before storing in airtight container.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: poor man's cabbage pickles
directions: Grind cabbage, onions, celery and bell peppers (or use food processor).
Mix 1 tablespoon salt and 1 cup flour with mustard and enough water to make a paste (not too thick).
Stir into pickles real good to thicken.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Put into jars that have been sterilized and seal.
These are almost as good as artichoke pickles.

title: vinegar chicken
directions: Wash and deskin chicken; put chicken in pan with a little water on the bottom.
Put pat of margarine on each piece of chicken.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bulkookee
directions: Trim fat off beef, cut diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
For ease in slicing, partially freeze beef for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: nectar syrup for ice cream sodas
directions: Place sugar and water into saucepan. Simmer until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and add condensed milk, flavorings and food coloring.
Stir well. Bottle and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: pie crust recipe
directions: Mix melted shortening and flour together; add milk and salt. Should be easy to handle.
Roll out on a floured surface and put into a pie pan.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle with red pepper and paprika. Cover.
Brown chicken well in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Remove chicken. Cook onions in fat until limp (not brown). Stir in soup and water.
Add chicken and cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over low heat. Stir occasionally. Stir in green peppers.
Cook 15 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve with rice.

title: stuffed chip steaks
directions: Mix all together.
Separate steaks on wax paper.
Put some of the stuffing in center of the steak and wrap around.
Place in a casserole dish.
Use either cream of mushroom or cream of celery soup, diluted with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over steaks and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, along with zucchini.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top, then bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas danish puff pastry
directions: In a bowl, cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour.
Sprinkle the cold water over the mixture.
Stir until blended.
Shape into a ball and divide in two.
Roll each piece into a 3 x 12-inch oblong.
Place them on a baking sheet.
Spread with your favorite jam and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor or mixing bowl. Mix until blended.
Roll in balls or desired shapes. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Store in refrigerator tightly covered.

title: texas junk
directions: Mix tomatoes and soup into ground beef.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, spread the Doritos.
Add meat mixture. Cover with grated cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes more.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream the shortening and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven until time is up.
Cook until cake leaves side of pan.

title: swiss cheese and onion soup
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add garlic, onion, mustard and salt.
Saute until tender.
Add stock.
Cover and simmer over low heat.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Blend together peanut butter, sugar, egg and oil.
Mix baking powder and flour.
Mix quickly together.
Add milk, just enough to make batter moist, but not too dry.
Bake in muffin pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar with corn and stir well.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour the mixture into greased casserole.
Dot with additional butter.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet dressing (stuffing)
directions: Moisten bread in water and just mix all together.
Double or triple for more.

title: shauna's basic truffles
directions: Heat cream just to boiling in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Remove from heat and whisk in chocolate and butter until smooth. Pour into shallow bowl.
Press plastic wrap directly onto chocolate and refrigerate 3 hours.
Scoop chocolate into 24 round teaspoon sizes and place on waxed paper.
Roll each between hands into balls.
Dredge in cocoa and toss gently to remove excess. Cover and refrigerate up to 1 week or freeze for 1 month.

title: candied pecans
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan with 2-inch sides.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar.
Fold in pecans.
Add to pan with melted butter; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Pour out onto wax paper.
Break apart; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked crispy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, onion powder, garlic salt, paprika and pepper.
Stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken pieces into oleo; roll in potato flake mixture to coat.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: low-fat pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing using directions on back of package.
Mix pasta and vegetables.
Add dressing and gently toss.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 3-quart baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Remove to cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Stir 2 to 3 times during baking.

title: date chews
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour, salt, dates and nuts.
Mix well.
In 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, melt butter.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut at once and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, butter, shortening and salt to mashed potatoes.
Stir when lukewarm.
Add yeast and potato water.
Let sit in a warm place until spongy.
Add beaten eggs and flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise until double in size.
Spread dough on 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Let rise again.
Punch holes in dough and fill with pieces of butter and brown sugar.
Dust top with cinnamon.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
When set, fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 15-inch pan, layer crackers and pudding alternately, ending with crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours, then frost.
Boil the last 4 ingredients until mixed well, then add confectioners sugar.
Spoon over chilled pudding mixture.

title: stuffed lettuce
directions: Hollow out center of lettuce, leaving at least a 1-inch shell. Beat cheeses and milk until smooth.
Add onion and mix thoroughly.
Stuff lettuce with mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Place half the bread in 9 x 13 Pyrex dish. Cover with cheese, then oysters. Top with remaining bread. Mix eggs and the oyster liqueur, then add enough milk to total 2 1/2 cups. Add salt and pepper. Pour liquid over the bread, cheese and oysters. Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours. Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked apples and cranberries
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 10 to 14.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Roll bread slices thin with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese on bread, then roll up into "fingers". Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Dip bread fingers in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar mix.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven until lightly browned and crunchy, about 20 to 25 minutes.
These can be frozen after baking and then rewarmed.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool and add vanilla, chocolate and cream.
Place in either plain or graham cracker crust and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve.

title: e-z mushroom green beans
directions: Put drained beans in saucepan.
Add a can of mushroom soup and milk.
Season to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: blueberry cheesecake squares
directions: Rinse and drain blueberries; set aside.
Thoroughly cut firm butter into muffin mix.
Set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remaining into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Blend sugar and softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla, one ingredient at a time.
Beat well.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle berries, then remaining 1/2 cup muffin mix and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chill well.
Cut in squares.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Turn pot on low in the morning and potatoes will be ready for supper.
(I use cream of chicken soup in place of Cheddar cheese soup.)

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix ingredients together in large container.
Put in small styrofoam cups and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Peaches may be added.

title: dilled mushroom sauce
directions: Heat butter in saucepan.
Add scallions and garlic; saute. Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat, stirring about 1 minute. Remove mixture from pan; set aside.
Add oil to saucepan and heat for a few seconds. Stir in flour and dill. Cook about 1 minute, stirring.
Slowly pour in milk and simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens enough to coat the back of a spoon.
Stir in mushroom mixture and serve hot. Good over vegetable dishes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check center with straw.
While still warm, prepare icing.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Clean out chicken.
Cut ends off lemons and prick with a fork or knife all over.
Sprinkle garlic, pepper and rosemary inside chicken liberally.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender.
This dip is delicious with raw vegetables.

title: easy fruit dessert
directions: For a sweet but nutritious no-fat dessert; put chopped fruit slices in a square cake pan.
Add in canned fruit.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar-flour and flake cereal.
If raisins are included, put in fruit part, not topping, as their skins can burn. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato biscuit
directions: Boil and mash the potatoes, having them free from lumps.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder;
add the potatoes and cut in the shortening.
Mix to a light dough with the egg and milk; roll out a little thinner than ordinary biscuit and bake in a hot oven. Serve as soon as done.

title: johnny salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together; add whipped topping.
Stir well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: soft brown bread
directions: Do not sift graham flour.
Mix everything together.
Old recipe says let stand 1 hour and bake for 1 hour in moderate oven. May be baked at once for 3/4 hour at 375°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine water, vinegar and egg.
Pour liquid into flour mixture and blend.
Roll out.
Bake crust at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 double crusts or 4 singles.

title: ervin's cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix batter and crumbs and press evenly in the pan.
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and then the peanut butter chips.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Press lightly.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Chill in pan on rack. Cut into bars.

title: ez peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Melt in microwave until blendable (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir ion mini marshmallows and raisins.
Fold into 9 x 9-inch square pan lined with foil.
Chill and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: german pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients with mixer until well mixed.
Add more milk to make very thin batter (3/4 to 1 cup).
Fry on very hot griddle with thin layer of shortening.

title: oriental style vegetables
directions: Boil chopped carrots for 6 minutes.
While cooking, mix soy sauce, sugar, lemon and ginger in a separate dish.
Add pea pods with carrots; cook 4 more minutes.
Drain vegetables and pour separate mixture over vegetables and serve.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken or pork chops
directions: Combine ingredients in boiler and heat to boiling.
Let mixture boil real good.
Stir frequently.
After mixture has boiled about 8 to 10 minutes, pour sauce over meat and set in oven until meat is real tender.
Spoon sauce over meat several times while cooking.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 350° for one hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: boatman stew
directions: Salt fish and let stand in refrigerator a few hours.
Make sauce, browning onion in oil.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, add fish and cook until done.
Serve over or with French bread.

title: honeyed chicken salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients.
Toss salad with dressing.
Chill. Best served within several hours of preparation.
If stored longer, drain off any liquids that accumulate.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except bread.
Blend well.
Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch rounds with a small biscuit cutter.
Spread each round with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot from the oven.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Fry bacon and crumble into kidney beans.
Saute vegetables in bacon drippings.
Cook until wilted, but not brown.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: aunt ellen's cherry salad
directions: Note: Put all ingredients in the refrigerator over night before preparation.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Mix in taco seasoning according to package directions.
Spread in 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Layer with sour cream taco sauce, and top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Add mushroom stems and fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place a paper towel on plate and arrange mushrooms in a circle on plate.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, rotating plate after 1 1/2 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine all and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix ground beef and Ragu sauce.
Mix eggs with cottage cheese.
Layer 2-3 times, ending with cheese.
Layer ground beef mixture in 9x13 dish.
Top with cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese, parmesan cheese and noodles.

title: breakfast apple pancake(dutch babies)
directions: Saute apples in butter, cinnamon and brown sugar until translucent (5 to 10 minutes).
Meanwhile, mix eggs and flour until smooth.
Blend in milk and sugar.
Put apple mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan and top with egg/milk batter.
Bake until pancake is puffy and golden.
Bake at 400° to 450° about 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Serves 4.

title: praline pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients; add pecan halves last.
Mix by spoon 20 beats.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, or until dark brown.
Let cool.

title: butter broccoli nuts
directions: Trim off ends of broccoli stems to make 3 inch spears with florets.
The stem ends of the broccoli are not used in this recipe.
Rinse broccoli with the florets in cold running water. Drain well and set aside.
Cut pepper into 1/2 inch pieces, and chop onion. Place butter in skillet
on medium heat, when butter melts stir in onion and 1/4 cup of water.
Cook for 3 minutes or until water evaporates.
Stir in peppers and almonds.
Cook mixture for 1 minute.
Place broccoli spear on top of onion mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and add 1/2 cup of water to skillet. Cover skillet and cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Boil soup and celery until tender.
Mix all ingredients. Simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine apple puree, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, lemon juice and cloves in saucepan.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring frequently.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield:
60 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and margarine. Then add flour and vanilla, mix well. Next add apples and nuts. Mix well, pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan and bake at approximately 350° until done.
About 30-35 minutes. Add glaze.

title: oysters on the grill
directions: Shuck and clean oysters and shells.
Place largest half shells in a pan; return oysters and prepare to dress.
For each oyster, add one drop hot sauce, two drops lemon juice, dash of pepper and a slice of cheese.
When grill is hot, place oysters directly on grill (no pan).
Cover grill; cook until cheese melts.
Carefully remove from grill; shells will be hot.
Enjoy!

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion, stirring to separate lumps; drain off fat.
Add soups, water and oregano.
Cool meat mixture slightly.
Mix with the noodles and chill overnight.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Leave in oven until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook to 238° on candy thermometer (soft ball).
Stir in marshmallow cream and beat until mixture is very thick (about 8 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased pan and let stand until firm.
Cut into squares with sharp, warm knife.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine undiluted soups, melted butter and almonds.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Mix rice with the remainder of the mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of soup-rice mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
Baste the chicken every 15 to 20 minutes with the reserved soup mixture. About 15 minutes before the end of the baking time, sprinkle the cheese over the chicken and allow it to brown.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots and onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour slaw dressing over cabbage mixture; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir well. Ladle slaw into jars.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust plastic storage caps.
Label and freeze.

title: unstuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Cook over low heat until onion is soft.
Add sage, pepper and salt.
Blend well.
Add crumbs and water.
Toss lightly until bread is slightly moistened.

title: ella's cream cheese frosting
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Soften margarine. Blend together remainder of ingredients.

title: choke cherry syrup
directions: Dissolve pectin in juice.
Add corn syrup and bring to a boil. Add sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine all chopped vegetables and sprinkle with 1/4 cup pickling salt.
Cover and cold water.
Let stand four hours. Drain, rinse and drain again.
Combine in large Dutch oven with sugar, vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal. Makes 4 pints.

title: 40th birthday yummies(mini chocolate chip pudding pies)
directions: Freeze dough for 1 hour.
Spray mini cupcake tins with Pam before each batch of cookies.
Preheat oven to 350°; cut dough into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices, then cut into quarters.
Place in tins and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, press a melon baller or spoon into center of each cookie to form a cup.
Cool in pans 5 to 7 minutes.
Pop out gently with a knife and cool completely.
Fill up two pastry bags, one with pudding and one with Cool Whip.
Fill each cup with pudding; top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, prick top with fork and pour can of cream of coconut and crushed pineapple.
If can has too much juice, do not use all of it.
When cold, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut over top. Keep refrigerated.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; beat until mixed.
Spread batter into baking dish.
Spoon filling into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: creole fish chowder, new orleans, 1916
directions: Cut fresh fish up.
Take potatoes and onion and cut into slices.
Wash salt pork and chop very fine.
Place pork into frying pan.
When hot, add sliced onion.
Smother lightly; add thyme, parsley, bay leaf, garlic (chopped fine) and peppers.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Pour over this the boiling water and add fish, tomatoes and the potatoes.
Season to taste and cover pan; let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: miniature meat turnovers
directions: In skillet, combine first 5 ingredients.
Brown well. Separate crescent dough and cut in half.
Place spoonful of mix in center of each triangle and fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake until golden (about 15 minutes at 370°).
Work on floured board.

title: baked corn
directions: Place 1 bag of corn in blender with milk, eggs and flour. Blend until creamy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place the second bag of corn; stir in blender and mix.
Cut butter into pats on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: guacamole tostaditas(tortilla chips topped with avocado)
directions: Cut each corn tortilla into 4 rounds with a 2 to 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Arrange the tortilla rounds in one layer on baking sheet, cover them with towel and let stand for 1 hour.
Fry in vegetable oil in a heavy skillet for 30 seconds in batches.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle them with salt.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add eggs, pumpkin, oil and buttermilk.
Mix all together and pour into coffee cans about 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and remove from cans.
(May use loaf pans.)

title: cream chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In pot, mix together chicken, cream of chicken soup and peas
and carrots; bring to boil.
Turn heat down; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sticky tomatoes
directions: Skin and core tomatoes and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours, then remove from oven and place on slow burner on stove.

title: jackie's hawaiian meat balls
directions: Make bite size meat balls from first 8 ingredients.
Using a large casserole, fry them until browned.
Add green pepper and onions and cook slowly for a few minutes.
When meat balls are done, add Hawaiian vegetables and about 3/4 of pineapple juice. Add more juice if necessary during cooking; sauce should be plentiful but not watery.
Steam for about one hour.
Then, thicken by blending flour into some of sauce until smooth and stirring mixture back into casserole.
Add the pineapple about 15 minutes before serving; if added too early it may camouflage the more delicate flavors.
I judge the amount of spices and ingredients to taste or guess, so you can juggle them, too.
Serve over rice flavored with sherry.
Great at buffet dinners.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream mixture together and
mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet and press
with
fork
to flatten into a cookie shape.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries; break up with a fork.
Stir occasionally.
When jello molds slightly, fold in whipped cream.
Pour in cooled crust.
Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar well. Add chocolate mixture.	Add
sifted
dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 10 x
13-inch
pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.	Cool in
pan.
Frost
with Hungarian Frosting.

title: peach jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, except Sprite. Mix well and freeze.
Make 1 or 2 days before serving. Take from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add Sprite then.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble up biscuits in bowl.
Add milk and 1 egg for each biscuit.
Add sugar and let stand until liquid is soaked up. Grease pan and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with chocolate sauce.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour on top of all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add all wet ingredients. Mix well.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° for cake, 20 minutes for cupcakes.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Sift flour and salt. Add sugar
and shortening.
Mix well.
Add as much warm water as needed
to	make
stiff dough.
Work well and put in large greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Make into rolls and	let rise
until
double
in
size.
Bake
at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbly.
Drain thoroughly. In chafing dish, melt cheeses.
Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onions.
Mix well.
Makes a large amount, but can be frozen.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and take chicken off bone (reserve broth). Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix mushroom soup, cream of chicken and 1 1/2 to 2 cups reserved broth.
Heat in saucepan and pour over chicken. Mix butter with stuffing and spread over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or onion soup

title: couscous and chicken salad
directions: Cook couscous according to package directions.
Set aside for 10 minutes.

title: fergie's potato salad
directions: Mix green peppers, small carrot, celery, sweet pickles, onions, radishes, salt, pepper, sugar and pickle juice in mixing bowl.
Add potatoes which have been boiled and cut in cubes.
Stir and mix with other ingredients.
Add one chopped or diced hard-boiled egg.
Stir and mix with long prong fork and big spoon. Add mustard and mayonnaise, stir.
Add celery leaves for decoration if desired.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In separate pan, melt butter; mix flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and 1 cup cheese.
Stir constantly until thick and cheese is melted.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: man-style meat and potatoes
directions: In skillet, brown onions and beef in butter until onions are tender.
Blend in soup, milk and 3/4 cup of cheese.
In casserole, arrange layers of potatoes and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sweet and sour water chestnuts(appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap each water chestnut with strip of bacon, securing with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Cover completely with sweet and sour sauce.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) spring-form pans. Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in walnuts, coconut, carrots and pineapple.
Pour into pans.
Bake on middle rack of oven for 50 minutes or until edges pull away and cake tester comes out clean.
Cool on cake rack for 3 hours.
Frost cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix all other ingredients, excluding nuts and chips.
Add margarine to mix and let cool.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Fold in Cool Whip. Make up pudding by adding a layer of wafers, a layer of bananas and a layer of sauce.
Makes 1 extra large bowl or 2 medium bowls of pudding.

title: apple goodie
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Combine with sugar, cinnamon, 1 heaping tablespoonful flour and salt.
Mix and place in square Pyrex dish. Mix rest of ingredients thoroughly and spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: scalloped eggplant beef casserole
directions: Cover eggplant with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain; set aside.
Saute onions, green pepper and ground beef in a large skillet over medium flame until meat is browned, stirring constantly.
Add eggplant and remaining ingredients, combining thoroughly.
Spoon into a lightly greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° gas oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer or until brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar and pepper sauce in stainless steel pot.
Bring to full boil over high heat.
Remove and set aside for 20 minutes.
Return to heat and bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add liquid pectin and food color.
Stir, mixing well.
Remove skim if necessary and pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal according to manufacturer's directions.
May be spread over cream cheese square or spread on round cracker for appetizer.
Yields 8 to 10 half pints.

title: easy easter eggs
directions: Any combination of the following can be added according to your taste:
coconut, walnuts, pecans, cherries or candied pineapple.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until thickens; add few drops red food coloring.
Let cool and add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt with fork.
Add shortening with fork until crumbly.
Beat together water, white vinegar and egg. Combine to flour mixture, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide into 4 or 5 portions.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least an hour.
When ready, roll out.
Patties can be frozen.

title: sorghum cookies
directions: Mix with hands (you can cool in refrigerator).
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
They will fall and be waxy.

title: mother's pecan roll
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients on low heat to form soft ball (do not overcook).
Add nuts and roll mixture in damp cloth.
Use buttered hands to form a long roll.
Let cool in cloth.
When cool cut in smaller rolls.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Combine the water, beans, salt, pepper, bay leaf and cloves in saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat 3 minutes less than package directions.
Drain; add sugar, vinegar, butter or fat, onion and bacon.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: fallen fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first five ingredients and pour mixture over melted margarine.
Mix last four ingredients and pour mixture in the middle of first mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes. Mixtures will be thin (especially the second).
Cool to a pudding.

title: cheesy broccoli and rice
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and broccoli.
Add salt and cook until tender.
Add cheese and stir.
Add milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir in rice.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pollo flauta
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and salt.
Add broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add lemon juice, parsley, onion, paprika, nutmeg and pepper.
Stir in chicken.
Cool slightly.
Warm tortillas until soft.
Place 1 tablespoon of chicken mixture on each tortilla; roll and secure with toothpick.
Fry in deep hot oil at 350° for 1 to 2 minutes, until crisp.
Serve with guacamole.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Then add salt and buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Combine vinegar and soda and add to mixture.
Just blend together.
Put into two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy turkey rice squares
directions: Substituting chicken broth for water, cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and butter.
Stir cheese and 2 tablespoons butter into hot rice.
Add spinach, onions and turkey and mix well.
Beat eggs well.
Add with 1 1/2 cups milk to rice mixture.
Blend lightly.
Turn into well-greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cut in squares and serve with cheese sauce.
To make cheese sauce, blend cheese soup with milk in saucepan and heat thoroughly.
That's all there is to it!

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Stir in food coloring. Set aside.

title: squash parmesan
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter until almost transparent.
Add sliced squash and continue to saute.
When squash is slightly browned and limp, remove from heat.
Serve with generous amounts of Parmesan cheese on top.

title: my mom's fudge
directions: Use a heavy pan; butter sides and bottom.
Add cocoa, sugar and salt; mix together.
Add syrup and milk; mix well.
Bring to a boil and stir until the soft ball forms in a cup of cold water.
Let cool; add oleo, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour into a buttered dish or pan.
Cut when cool.
Store in airtight container.
This is really creamy!

title: carol's brownie drops
directions: Melt together shortening & chocolate squares. Add sugar, buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla. Blend well. Sift together dry ingredients & add to chocolate mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop from teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes. Glaze while warm.

title: meat loaf in potato ring
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and garlic.
Shape meat into 7-inch round loaf.
Overlap cut potatoes in ring around loaf.
Sprinkle with onions.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, gravy mix and water.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread peaches and syrup in a 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle on nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sprinkle dry cake mix in an even layer on top of peaches.
Cut butter into thin slices and cover top of cake mix completely.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: banana swirl pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and milk well in large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat until blended well.
Chill few minutes and stir in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Line glass bowl with wafers and bananas. Add some chocolate syrup and then some pudding mix.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding mix.
Drizzle syrup over top and swirl with knife.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: jalapeno vegetable chowder
directions: In a 5-6 qt pan, combine oil, garlic, onion, cumin, oregano, chilies (use smaller amount for milder flavor, more if you like it hotter), and bell pepper.
Stir over medium heat until onion is limp.
Stir in flour, then broth.
Bring to boiling; add sweet potato.
Cover and simmer until potato is tender when pierced, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil and cool.
Clean green beans and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Steam for 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Drain and flake tuna.
Place macaroni, green beans, raw zucchini, carrots and tuna in medium bowl.
In a small bowl, place olive oil, vinegar, salt,
pepper, oregano and basil.
Stir with a whisk.
Pour over ingredients in bowl and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry, lemon juice, white wine, ginger and nutmeg to make sauce.
Put broccoli in buttered casserole.
Arrange chicken over broccoli and pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar and buttered bread crumbs on top if desired.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Good served over rice.

title: stephanie mclaughlin's cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Break up cranberry sauce with spoon and stir into jello until dissolved.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake 30 minutes uncovered at 400 degrees.

title: pecan pie(my mother's)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add the other ingredients and stir well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done.
Start baking at 400° for a short time, then lower to 350° or 300° at last.

title: party chicken
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased dish with dried beef. Top with chicken breasts. Mix soup and cream cheese and pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: all american jello dessert(great for 4th of july)
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls until completely dissolved.
Stir 1 cup cold water into each bowl.
Pour into 2 separate 13 x 9-inch pans. Refrigerate at least 3 hours until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes (may cut a star out of each color for decoration on top).
Put into clear bowl, blue Jell-O on bottom, Cool Whip, blueberries, pound cake, strawberries, Cool Whip, red Jell-O and a dash of Cool Whip on top and stars if desired.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Saute eggplant in bacon drippings.
Place in casserole dish. Saute onions and stir in tomatoes, parsley, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over eggplant.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cube 5 or 6 slices of bread, spread on a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine together chicken, onion, green pepper, margarine, celery, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over bread.
Cube 4 or 5 more slices bread and spread over chicken.
Combine eggs and milk. Mix and pour over mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: angel roll
directions: Mix by hand until mixture is moist.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in cookie sheet (lined with wax paper).
Take out of pan when cool to touch; roll up in towel (paper towel).
Put in freezer for 20 minutes; unroll.

title: sweet peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, simmer for 10 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan and dust with flour; tap out excess.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add in order: sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in carrots, coconut, walnuts and pineapple until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center springs back when pressed lightly with fingertip.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Good with cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix sauce, soup and broth.
Layer chicken, Fritos, onion and cheese.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious cocoa brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light.
Gradually add flour and cocoa which are sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: jennifer's brownies
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large bowl; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: feline favorite
directions: Next
time
you use tuna, save a small portion	of
the tuna and
juice	and add to dry cat chow with a	little	warm water. Mix well and serve.
It is a special treat	all
cats love!

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and mix well.
Pack into an oiled 9 x 5-inch pan, then turn out onto oiled shallow baking pan and finish shaping with hands.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and top loaf with overlapping cheese slices.
Return loaf to oven until cheese softens.
Serve plain or with catsup or tomato sauce.
Serves 8.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Brown, rinse and drain hamburger, bell pepper and onion.
Pour and mix all ingredients (including hamburger, pepper and onion) into a 9 x 5-inch sheet pan.
Cook at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until moistened. Add vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup pecans.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Right before serving put on a 16 oz. bottle Western dressing. If you wish top with scoops of sour cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Slip noodles into boiling water (add 1 tablespoon cooking oil so noodles won't stick together).
Simmer meat with onion and garlic; drain meat mixture.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan make layers starting with meat, then noodles, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese; continue to layer.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 40 minutes in a 450° oven.
You may also add layers of cottage cheese in this.

title: party egg salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and curry powder; beat well with rotary beater or blender.
Pour into freezing tray or metal loaf pan. Chill in freezing unit until firm, about 1 inch from pan edge, but still soft in center (about 20 minutes).
Beat with electric mixer or blender until fluffy and thick.
Fold in eggs, celery, green pepper and parsley.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch pan or dish. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper. Add sugar and vinegar. Cook green beans to a boil and then drain. Place in casserole and pour onion mixture over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: tahitian chicken with pineapple
directions: Brush chicken with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange skin-side down in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes, until chicken begins to brown.
Combine syrup drained from pineapple with broth, soy sauce, lemon juice and cornstarch. Pour over chicken.
Cover and continue baking about 25 minutes, until tender.
Uncover; add pineapple chunks, green onion and pea pods.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: poi palau(sweet potato poi)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes, peel and mash.
Keep hot.
Heat coconut milk and pour over potatoes and mix to make mixture the consistency of poi.
Add sugar and salt and mix well.
Serve in individual bowls.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, then drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine macaroni, sour cream, onions, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spoon into 15 x 9-inch lightly greased pan or dish. Sprinkle cheese crackers evenly over macaroni mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Crumble raw ground beef in a bowl.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce, 1 egg, salt and pepper to taste and crushed crackers.
Mix well. Spread flat on waxed paper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; place in a mixing bowl.
Place butter, Crisco, cocoa and water into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
When reaches boiling point, pour over first mixture and stir.
Add buttermilk and baking soda.
Pour into mixture.
Add slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water over medium heat until it forms hard ball or cracks in water (approximately 20 minutes).
Pour into stiff egg whites by thin stream and beat with mixer.
Remove and beat by hand until thick and dull.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool before storing in airtight container.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Makes 2 cups dry mix, enough for 6 quarts tea.

title: *beef with wine
directions: Coat
meat in mixture of flour and paprika.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet. Remove to Dutch oven. Add 2 cups red wine, bay leaf, 2 cloves garlic, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
In the skillet, add remaining 2 tablespoons butter, cooking butter until brown. Add tomato paste and stir with butter until blended and tomato paste is slightly brown.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and blend together. Add to Dutch oven.
Simmer contents, adding extra 1/2 cup water if necessary,
until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook carrot, onion and squash in boiling water 5 minutes. Drain and combine with soup and sour cream.
Mix melted butter in stuffing.
Spread 1/2 stuffing in bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon in the vegetables and cover with the rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yoffles
directions: Toast the frozen waffle, then butter it.
Microwave waffle on High for 20 seconds.
(Ask your mom or dad to help you.)
Spread with your favorite flavor of yogurt and cut into bite size pieces.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and lemon chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges begin to brown, about 10 minutes.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat eggs; add vanilla, oil and apples.
Combine flour mixture with egg mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins (if desired).
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas and nuts.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or pour into miniature loaf pans and bake about 20 minutes.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine in top of double boiler.
Sift confectioners sugar and cocoa together until thoroughly mixed and no lumps remain.
This is very important.
Mix sugar mixture into melted margarine and cheese, blending thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Add vanilla and nuts (optional) and blend again.
Press into two 9 x 13-inch pans that have been greased.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a large skillet and saute onion, garlic, mushrooms, green pepper and corn.
Add beans, tomatoes, spices, wine and salt and simmer 30 minutes.
Put a layer of tortillas in an oiled casserole.
Top with a layer of sauce, 3 tablespoons grated cheese and 3 tablespoons cheese/yogurt mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of sauce.
Add a little of the cheese/yogurt mixture and garnish with olives.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla drop cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and margarine.
Add egg, vanilla, soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Bring 5 cups of water to boil.
Add rice; cook for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add instant soup mix and cheese; dissolve well.
Saute sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in Pyrex baking dish; bake for about 10 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook until thick and bake in unbaked shell.

title: flan
directions: In a small heavy saucepan over medium heat, cook sugar, stirring after it bubbles until it caramelizes.
Pour into an ovenproof mold.
Swirl to coat the bottom and sides.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pie filling and pineapple together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in sour cream and pecans. Place on top of prepared Jell-O and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled crust.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and bacon; drain and let cool.
Add eggs 1 at a time to meat mixture.
Roll dough into an oblong shape (1 loaf at a time).
Spread 1/2 meat mixture on each loaf of bread dough. Sprinkle each loaf with 1/2 of cheese.
Roll each loaf up like a cinnamon roll.
Bake on cookie sheet 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: no passover chicken
directions: Mix the soup mix with water and cook until onions are tender. Add the peach or apricot preserves and dressing.
Stir until preserves melt.
Place the chicken in pan or dish and pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, chicken broth, garlic and 1/2 the onions in a large soup pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are very soft, 3 hours or more.
Add more broth if needed. In a skillet, saute remaining onions in oil until tender.
Add chilies and seasoning and mix thoroughly.
Add to bean mixture. Add chicken and continue to simmer 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese and any of the following:

title: peach marmalade
directions: Wash, peel and slice peaches in quarters.
Grate orange rinds.
Peel oranges and cut into thin slices.
Combine peaches, oranges, grated orange rinds, lemon juice and sugar in a large heavy pot.
Boil mixture until syrup is thick and fruit is transparent, stirring frequently.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: quick pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger in skillet, drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and chopped vegetables.
Place tomato sauce or stewed tomatoes (with juice) on the bread.
Place ground beef and/or vegetable mixture on the bread.
Place cheese on top of the filling.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Early in day or day before:
Make barbecue sauce by combining, in saucepan, salt, pepper, tomato juice, Cayenne pepper, mustard, bay leaf, Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar, garlic and salad oil.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Refrigerate.
About 1 and one half hour before serving, preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange chicken in single layer in shallow oven-proof pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Arrange onions on chicken. Pour on barbecue sauce. Bake, uncovered, basting often, 1/2 hour. Turn. Bake, basting often, 45 minutes or until fork tender.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, vanilla, sour cream and eggs and mix for 4 minutes.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts together. Pour a little batter in a Bundt cake pan and spread the nut mix; repeat until ingredients are gone.
Mix together well and put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add cranberry sauce and stir.
Add other ingredients; mix and congeal.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix thoroughly; add hot water until soft dough is formed. Roll into rectangle until very thin.
Cut in squares.
Add to boiling broth and cook until done, about 20 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour half of the mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir together brown sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle half of the mixture over the cake.
Pour in remaining cake mix and top with the rest of the brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 275° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Glaze the cake with the powdered sugar, vanilla and milk mixed together.

title: pea salad
directions: Put in layers in casserole dish.

title: chicken curry
directions: Add oil to wok and preheat (high).
Add onion, garlic and lemon.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove mixture.
Stir-fry chicken (half at a time) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove.
Set aside 1 tablespoon of oil in wok.
Add sweet potatoes and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add carrots.
In small bowl, stir water, brown sugar, curry, sesame oil, salt and pepper.
Stir into wok.
Boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir onion mix, chicken and coconut milk in wok. Cook over medium heat until done.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Heat oil one-inch deep to 375° in a large skillet.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Dip each onion ring into batter.
Fry rings about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Drain and cover with water.
Bake at 300°, covered, until soft.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet on waxed paper in freezer.
After frozen, store in plastic bag in freezer.
Thaw about 20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes to 25 minutes.

title: french ham
directions: Place meat in shallow pan.
Combine Coca-Cola and brown sugar and pour over ham.
Spread mustard over ham also.
Stick cloves in fat part of ham.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Brown lightly in butter. Saute onions and mushrooms. Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Top with favorite cheese.

title: coconut philly bonbons
directions: Place cream cheese in a bowl and cream it until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend the sugar into it.
Add vanilla and salt and mix until well blended.
Form into balls, using 1 tablespoon of mixture for each.
Roll in the coconut; chill until firm.

title: ham and cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, horseradish and onion together.
Pat ham dry on both sides with paper towel.
Take 1 slice of ham and spread mixture on it.
Place another slice of ham on top and spread mixture on again.
Roll lengthwise as a jelly roll.
Roll in aluminum foil and twist edges.
Freeze in refrigerator.
Take out 1 hour before use.
Slice in 1/4 inch pieces.

title: frozen fruit juice punch
directions: Add water to dilute frozen juices as directed on cans. Combine juices and water.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 14 punch cups.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables and black pepper.
Mix salad dressing and cheese. Stir into vegetables.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Put roast and sauce into crock-pot in the morning and cook all day.
(You can even use a frozen roast.)
Serve over cooked pasta shells with salad and bread.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Add milk slowly.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add egg yolks (slightly beaten) and cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add butter.
When cool, add vanilla. Pour into a baked crust.
Cover with meringue or whipped cream.

title: microwave chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix margarine, soup, stuffing and hot water.
Pour over chicken, microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Cover until ready to serve.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: shrimp sandwiches
directions: Mash shrimp and add desired amount of mayonnaise; mix the rest of ingredients.
Great as finger sandwiches on very thin bread.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown chuck and sausage.
Fill all cans with water and add with tomato paste and puree to skillet.
Heat slowly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 3 to 4 hours. Can be kept in refrigerator or frozen.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat as usual.
After cooling, slice thin.
To pan juices, add water, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place the sliced meat in the juices, cover with beer, brandy and soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake 1/2 hour at 300°.
Serve on buns or hard rolls.

title: fried beets
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and fry about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham butt sandwich
directions: Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour with butt sliced into sauce.

title: sharon's soy sauced chicken (whole)
directions: Wipe the chicken dry with a paper towel. Dilute soy sauce one to one with plain water.
Add onion and sugar.
Add the chicken. Using medium heat, cook the chicken with a cover.
The heat should be strong enough to bring all the mixture to a boil, bubbling around and over the chicken, but not too strong as to evaporate the mixture too quickly.
Turn the chicken every five minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Melt butter in bottom of skillet.
Pour corn into butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Add water and simmer until tender.
When tender, allow to cook until liquid is gone.

title: edward's cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Let set overnight.
Roll in pecans after it sets.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix together, bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cool.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Layer in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish. Add layer of chopped chicken on this.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Cover with layer of soup mixture. Cover all this with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Pat firmly in 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar; gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add small amount to egg yolks; stir in remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla and cool slightly.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and strawberries, finish with pudding.
May top with meringue or wafers.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water in a large bowl.
Add remaining sugar, salt, shortening, egg and 1 cup warm water; mix well.
Stir in 2 cups flour, mix, then remaining flour.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and congeal.
Soften cream cheese and blend with sour cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of congealed mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in large container.
Use as needed. Three heaping teaspoons of the mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: cauli-broc salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in salad bowl.
Add Italian dressing, just enough to coat vegetables lightly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp and sausage boil
directions: In large pot, bring 3 quarts of water to boil with the Old Bay seasoning and shrimp cocktail sauce.
Add potatoes; boil 10 minutes.
Add the corn, onion and sausage and boil for additional 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and boil until they turn pink.
Pour off majority of water and turn mixture into a large serving dish. Provide small dishes for the dipping sauces and dinner plates for the main dish.
An easy and fun dish to prepare and eat.
Pass the napkins! Serves 4.

title: russian salad
directions: Combine with enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to bind without being too moist.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Line casserole with dried beef.
Arrange chicken breasts in casserole on dried beef.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Don't let chicken dry out.

title: beef stew
directions: In an 8-quart pot, heat all vegetables, salsa, onion and tomatoes. Do not drain vegetables. Roll stew meat in flour and brown in skillet. When meat has a crisp outer coating, place in pot. Slowly boil, covered, for 30 minutes. Stew is done when potatoes are soft on the inside.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add crushed vanilla wafers which milk has been added to. Add the coconut and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: mom's cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar and butter.
Lay in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save some crumbs for garnish.

title: fun fudge
directions: Melt in microwave until barely warm the Hershey bars.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Drop by teaspoon into flaked coconut or graham cracker crumbs.
Roll.
Place on waxed paper and set aside until firm. These can be refrigerated or frozen.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange apples in unbaked pie shell.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with the flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pass the whipped cream. Delicious; never fails!

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend 3 top ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mash and mix last 2 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: crock-pot curried chicken(4 to 5 servings)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot. Combine curry, garlic, butter, bouillon, onion and 1/2 cup peach syrup.
Pour curry sauce over chicken and cover pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Remove chicken from pot.
Turn control to high. Stir in prunes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into sauce in pot.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add peaches.
Serve chicken with sauce.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Beat in sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in oiled and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: scandinavian relish
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix and marinate in mixture of oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fruit tea
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Use part of water to boil tea bags.
Bring to boil and cut off.
Take rest of water and pour over tea bags (use remaining gallon water).
Take 2 cups more water and 2 cups sugar, heaping tablespoonful of cinnamon (or 4 to 6 cinnamon sticks) and 1 tablespoon whole cloves. Mix together in separate pot; boil for 15 minutes.
Together add sugar mixture into tea mixture all in with juices.
Let set for 2 hours and then store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold.

title: deep-dish peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon peaches in pie shell.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and salt in a small bowl.
Add egg, egg whites and sour cream, stirring until well blended.
Spoon over peaches.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and remaining flour in a small bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over pie. Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Let chicken sit in this mixture for 15 minutes.
Roll chicken in flour.
In a large skillet, fry chicken pieces in cooking oil.
Drain.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Follow directions for 8 or 9-inch cake; bake and cool.
Slice to make 4 layers.
Thaw coconut; mix all ingredients together (well) with fork.
Refrigerate for 3 days before cut.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Bring sugar and water to a soft-ball stage. Remove from fire. Add cinnamon, salt, vanilla and pecans. Stir until sugared. Good for Christmas presents.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In bowl mix cornstarch and garlic salt.
Dip chicken pieces in egg, then into cornstarch mixture. Fry chicken pieces until golden brown.
Then thoroughly drain and set aside chicken.

title: frost on the pumpkin pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Set aside 1 Tbsp. for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 7-9 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Addition of a ham bone is the most important donation to the pot, for it adds real color and flavor not possible to achieve otherwise.
The next most important thing is to buy small, dark red beans, not kidney beans.
However, it is possible to substitute kidney beans.
Just don't expect to get quite the true flavor.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, then add flour.

Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately to sugar mixture with buttermilk, beginning and ending with the flour. Beat egg whites until very stiff and fold into cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, 1/3 cup of the sauce and the remaining ingredients.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spread remaining tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour; add milk, egg yolks, butter and pecans.
Cook
over
medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top
with	the
2 egg whites beaten with 4 tablespoons sugar for meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup and cheese together in microwave dish.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Drain green beans and mushrooms. Add to cheese mixture.
Stir until beans and mushrooms are coated. Microwave for 3 minutes or until beans are hot.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese ball made simple
directions: In bowl, mix together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add a little grated onion with juice and the rest should be finely chopped.
Season to taste with garlic and chili powder.
Add 3 or 4 dashes of Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Roll into ball or log shape.
May be rolled in finely chopped pecans.

title: texas okra gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan, put chicken winglets, onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, hot sauce and water.
Cook about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add sausage, shrimp, rice and okra; add more tomato and water, if needed.
Cook on slow fire until done.
(The dish should have the consistency of thick soup.) Serve with crackers.

title: rhubarb-pineapple jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, drained pineapple and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Boil until rhubarb is tender; add gelatin.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal or place in suitable freezer containers and freeze.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put marshmallows over baked bars.
Bake in oven for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and Rice Krispies.
Spread on cake.
Refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat powdered sugar, eggs and margarine together until smooth. (Double for thicker layer.) Using a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer ingredients in order that they are listed.
Chilling overnight makes a great difference in the taste.

title: ripe tomato chili sauce
directions: Skin and cook tomatoes.
Drain well in colander.
Chop onions and peppers; add to drained tomatoes.
Add all spices, sugar and vinegar.
Cook 30 minutes or until thick.

title: white muffin biscuits
directions: Mix and drop in greased muffin tin.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Prepare and cook corn bread mix. Crumble corn bread; add milk and let soak.
Mix pepper, celery, onion and margarine and add soup, sage, eggs, salt and pepper. Mix all together.
Use 1/4 of the stick of margarine to grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour dressing into dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pan ukakku(finnish pancake)
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 9 x 12-inch pan in oven.
Pour in mix.
I add fresh sliced fruit. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve like pancakes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the salad in this order:
Lettuce, cauliflower, onion, chopped bacon and cheese.
Lightly frost the Miracle Whip over the top of the salad without mixing it with the cheese, then sprinkle with the sugar.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight, then stir together before serving.
Serves 8.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour and sugar. Beat in egg and milk to desired consistency.

title: ants on a log
directions: First, clean the celery, then cut off ends.
Now cut the celery in 2-inch pieces.
Spread the honey on the bottom.
Spread the peanut butter on with a butter knife or a spoon.
Last, put the raisins on.
Put on tray or plate to serve.

title: mothers pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at at time, beating well after each.
Sift flours together.	Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Do not over heat.
Bake 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Remove skin from chicken legs.
Place chicken in baking dish with marinade, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning chicken occasionally.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Mix egg with sugar.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Press with spoon on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops and wild rice(or substitute chicken breasts)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour in and place meat on top; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies(microwavable)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add salt.
Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts and stir to blend well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square micro-safe pan or dish.
Microwave at High power for about 3 minutes.
Let rest for 3 minutes. Microwave at High power for another 3 minutes and let rest for 3 more minutes.
Finally microwave at High power for 2 more minutes or until batter is set and done to your liking.
Let rest in pan for a couple of minutes or until almost cool.
Cut into squares. Remove from pan and garnish with nuts or powdered sugar.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together and add to slaw.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Toast almonds in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
In bowl, toss slaw, crushed noodles and almonds.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Simmer squash and onion until tender in small amount of water.
Drain remaining liquid, once squash is tender.
Add to this a can of stewed tomatoes (chopped).
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Add sliced cheese to this.
Let cheese melt.
Sit for 10 minutes on very low heat until ready to serve.

title: gablehouse zucchini bisque(soup)
directions: Chop and cook onion in butter until clear and soft, but not browned.
Wash and slice zucchini.
Combine onion, zucchini and chicken broth in heavy saucepan and bring to boil, then simmer for 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Add the seasonings and put mixture into blender to puree until smooth.
Add half and half; adjust seasonings to taste and reheat, but do not boil.
Serve immediately, garnished with grated Cheddar cheese and a dab of sour cream.

title: pat's grandma's caramels
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together 10 minutes.
Over low heat, cook additional half and half and butter.
Make sure butter is melted and mixture is hot.
At end of 10 minutes, pour cream and butter mixture slowly with first mixture.
Do not let the first mixture stop boiling.
Continue boiling over high heat for 15 minutes, stirring continually.
Cook on lower heat until candy hardens in ice cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into buttered pan 1 inch deep.
Cut into squares when cold and wrap in wax paper.

title: dilled relish
directions: Mix sugar, salt, dill weed, vinegar and water.
Bring to boil, let cool slightly to steep out flavor.
Slice 2 large Bermuda onions and 4 medium cucumbers (do not peel cucumbers).
Using a cabbage slaw cutter, make nice even slices.
Use 3 cans mushroom buttons, 1 medium can pitted black olives, drained well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni dinner (as directed on package); add frozen peas, tomatoes, eggs (some eggs may be used to garnish top with if desired), onion and salad dressing.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
After chilled, more salad dressing may need to be added.

title: corn meal chicken nuggets
directions: Combine
corn
meal,
chili powder and cumin; mix well. Add chicken
and
toss to coat well with mixture.
In a large skillet heat
oil
over
medium
heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring frequently 7 to 8 minutes or until chicken is browned on all sides and done in middle.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Heat oven
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Mix
all ingredients until moistened; stir vigorously 30 seconds.
Pour
batter into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick
inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove
from
pan.
Cool
completely before slicing. Makes 1 loaf (16 slices).

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: tiramisu(italian dessert)
directions: Blend cheese, 3 tablespoons coffee, Cool Whip and powdered sugar; mix and set aside.
Dip ladyfingers in this mixture of 1 1/2 cups coffee, sugar and liquor, on one side only.
Place dry side down in a dish, spread 1/2 mixture of cream and cheese and layer cookies, layer again cream cheese and cookies.
Then put cocoa or pieces of a Hershey bar on top.
Chill before you serve.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fillets in greased baking dish and dot with oleo. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all. Pour into unbaked shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour and cocoa until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar, then water and eggs yolks; set aside.

title: honey sand balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together the butter (not margarine), powdered sugar and honey.
Add the flour, nuts (optional), vanilla and salt (optional).
Mix thoroughly, using hands, if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press 1 1/2 inches apart on a well-greased cookie sheet, otherwise they will stick. Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes (or until cookies are lightly brown).
While still warm from the oven, roll the cookies in the extra powdered sugar.
Place them on a plate to cool.
When completely cool, roll again in the powdered sugar and serve.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: basil swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces.
Drain marinade from artichokes into skillet.
Brown meat in marinade.
When browned, pour fat from skillet.
Add Beau Monde and basil; pour tomatoes and one cup wine over meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Remove to serving plate.
Add artichoke hearts to pan juices.
Mix 1/4 cup wine with arrowroot and stir into pan gravy until it thickens.
Serve over meat.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Place 2 cups cabbage in greased, large casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, carrots and rest of cabbage.
Place hamburger in patties on layered vegetables.
Cut sausage into 2-inch strips.
Arrange between patties.
Pour water in.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover top of layered vegetables and meat with ketchup.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until done at 375°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Let freeze 8 hours, or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: swirl of chocolate cheesecake
directions: Stir vanilla wafer crumbs and butter until thoroughly blended; press into sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine chocolate (broken into sections) and 1/4 cup evaporated milk in small saucepan; place over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl until smooth; blend in sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until blended.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Remove 1 cup batter; stir into melted chocolate.
Pour chocolate batter into crust.
Carefully pour remaining vanilla batter over chocolate batter. Gently swirl batter with a spoon.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes or just until center is set.
Cool; chill thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole #3
directions: Steam broccoli in
salt
water.
Cut
in 1-inch chunks. Set aside.
Cook
rice
according to package.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Mix both soups in pepper and onion.
Mix well. Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour in casserole dish and bake until heated thoroughly.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Combine egg whites, heavy cream, confectioners sugar, vanilla extract and food coloring.
Mix thoroughly.
Add butter until well blended.
Roll into small balls and arrange on waxed paper.
Press each to flatten with tines of a fork that has been dipped in confectioners sugar.
Let stand overnight to form a crust.
Store layered with wax paper in an airtight container.
May be frozen for several months.
Makes 6 dozen quarter size mints.
