title: chicken spectacular
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add rice and simmer 20 minutes.
Add onion to rice and cook 5 minutes.

title: chuck's disciples favorite cookie(raisin oatmeal cookies)
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
(To soften the raisins, boil in 1/2 cup water.) Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs together; add sugar a little at a time.
Add salt, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Pour into ice cream maker and mix.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup; add gelatine and cream cheese.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut very well.
Mash to get all brine out of kraut. Add kraut, green pepper, onion, celery in bowl.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil - mix well. Add to kraut mixture.
Let stand overnight to marinate.

title: cranberry fruit ring
directions: Make jello with hot water; add cold water or juice.
When slightly thickened, add other ingredients.
Place in mold to set.

title: dieter's apple-celery-carrot salad
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Serve over fresh alfalfa or bean sprouts and watercress, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: orange velvet pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Mix all ingredients together, except Cool Whip, which is added last.
After all ingredients are added together, put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: mashed yams with carrots and apples
directions: Put yams, carrots, prunes, and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cover, and simmer for 25 minutes, or until tender.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Blend part of the water and all of the celery together.
Add to the rest of the water and place in large pot.
Run knife in the cans of green beans and carrots to chop them up.
Add all ingredients to pot.
Crumble the ground beef (uncooked) and add it to the pot.
Add salt and pepper if desired.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line
a 14-inch pizza pan with cookie slices, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cool crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
Glaze with combined preserves and water.
Chill.

title: corn flake christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add marshmallows and green cake coloring.
Add corn flakes and stir all together.
Press mixture into 1/4 measuring cup.
Turn out and punch a hole in the center. Press red hots into finished wreaths for the finishing touch. Makes 16 wreaths.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix; mold with hands into desired shape.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
When ready to serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter with chocolate over low heat; cool.
Place remaining butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Attach bowl and beater.

Turn to speed 2 (or stir) on electric mixer and mix for 30 seconds, then increase to speed 6 (or cream) for 2 minutes. Reduce to speed 4 (or blend) and add eggs, one at a time, beating 15 seconds after each.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Add butter and chocolate.
Turn to speed 2 and mix for 30 seconds. Reduce to stir speed and add flour, salt and nuts; mix until well blended, about 30 seconds.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into 2 inch squares.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: old fashioned brownies
directions: Beat eggs lightly with spoon.
Stir in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add shortening and chocolate.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Do not beat at any time.
Spread mixture in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Brownies should be soft.
Let cool in pan.
Yields 18 to 24 bars.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine pecans and citron.
Dredge in 1/3 cup of flour to coat evenly.
Set aside.
Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and next 5 ingredients, alternating with applesauce. Begin and end with flour mixture.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and coffee.
Mix well.
Stir in pecan and citron mixture.

title: pineapple orange ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jello and orange soda. Heat jello and orange soda but DO NOT BOIL. After heating and jello dissolves, mix with other ingredients in ice cream container. Fill container 3/4 full with regular milk. Freeze.

title: walnut carrot cake
directions: Chop 1/2 cup walnuts fine.
Grease 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans well.
Sprinkle each with about 2 1/2 tablespoons walnuts to coat. Chop remaining walnuts a little more coarsely; set aside.
Resift flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil and spices.
Beat at high speed until light and well mixed.
Add half of flour mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add milk, then remaining flour.
Stir in carrot and chopped walnuts.
Divide batter evenly in cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand in pans on wire racks to cool.
When cold, frost with a butter cream frosting.
Decorate with walnut halves.

title: mama's chicken pastry
directions: Put flour in round basin.
Make well and pour in hot water. Add vinegar and mix as you would for biscuits.
Form into one or two balls.
Sprinkle cloth with flour.
Roll dough from middle to thin pastry.
Cut into strips 6-inches long and 3-inches wide. Have chicken broth boiling.
Place leg bones on bottom of pot to prevent sticking.
Add a few slices at a time until all are in pot.
Cook for a very few minutes.
Add chicken.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices and chill.
Chill ginger ale before serving. Mix together over crushed ice.
Serves 25.
May add orange sherbet.

title: rhubarb-cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, nutmeg, flour and butter to beaten eggs.
Beat smoothly.
Pour over rhubarb in a 9-inch crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and serve on lettuce leaf or in a bowl.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together for crust and press in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Add by layers: bananas, Eagle Brand milk, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: creamy mashed potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first four ingredients. Spoon half mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 can French fried onions and Cheddar cheese. Top with remaining mixture. Bake 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and cheese. Bake 5 minutes until golden brown.

title: mae's candy
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; chill enough to shape into small balls, then chill overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and Baker's chocolate and 1/2 block paraffin in top of double boiler over low heat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and peeled oranges in the food processor. Add sugar to cranberries and oranges.
Let mixture set for 2 hours.
Drain pineapple; save the juice.
Grind celery, apples and pineapple in with the cranberry mixture.
Make jello with juice and water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Mix all ingredients together and chill in mold or dish.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt until blended.
Gradually stir in 1 quart of milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats the back of a spoon.
Do not boil.
Pour into a large bowl and stir in vanilla, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and remaining milk.
Will be like a custard.
Refrigerate until well chilled, approximately 3 hours.
To serve, beat cream until soft peaks form.
Fold whipped cream into custard mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: stuffed pork roast
directions: Split pork roast through middle.
Stuff with equal amounts of the preceding ingredients (depending on size of roast).
Bake according to size.

title: hot german cabbage
directions: Combine sugar, onion, caraway seed, dry mustard, pepper and vinegar.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Saute cabbage and apple over medium heat for 3 minutes. Stir in vinegar mixture and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pears, 1 cup coconut and eggs.
Blend and beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven; bring butter, sugar and milk to boil in small saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and stir in remaining coconut and nuts.
Spoon over hot cake.
Serve warm or cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Use Granny Smith apples.
Bake in Bundt pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir together and mix well.
Blend in apples and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool on a paper bag, this holds moisture.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; drain well.

title: boder's banana split ice cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into shell, distributing them evenly. Spoon ice cream over bananas. Cover well with plastic wrap and freeze overnight or until solid. When ready to serve, cut pie into 10 or 12 servings. Garnish each piece with a dollop of fudge. Top pieces with whipped cream, pecans and cherries. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana bread or peach bread
directions: Put together in order listed. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 45 minutes in a greased and papered loaf pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Microwave broccoli tips for 1 to 2 minutes on Medium.
Mix early in a.m. or the night before:
sugar, mayo, vinegar and bacon grease.
Combine with broccoli mixture.

title: wheat pizza crust
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add the sugar and salt.
Stir in whole wheat flour; beat well.
Add all-purpose flour; beat until smooth.
Knead 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Divide dough into two parts.
This makes 2 (12-inch) crusts.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Coat fryer pieces with flour.
Place in casserole.
Mix Coke, catsup and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: california stir-fry beef and asparagus
directions: Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Place in a shallow dish.
Combine 2 teaspoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sherry and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; pour over steak and marinate 10 minutes.
Remove steak from marinade.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil, then dry ingredients, vanilla, nuts and dates.
Bake at 300°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Stir sugar into eggs well.
Add heavy cream and then sweet milk.
Slowly add brandy.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.

title: creamiscle cake
directions: Make the orange cake according to directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, according to time.
Cool.
Poke holes with toothpick in the cake.
Dissolve 1 package of jello with 1 cup of boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour over cake and refrigerate.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cabbage; stir and chill.

title: magic crust broccoli pie
directions: Layer the broccoli, ham or chicken and cheese in a well oiled 9-inch pie plate.
Blend the remaining ingredients in a blender, food processor or with an electric hand mixer.
Pour over the cheese layer.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until creamy and smooth; set aside.
Place 1 vanilla cookie wafer in muffin tin inside cupcake paper.
Place cheese mixture on top of cookie (about 1/2 full) and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Place your choice of fruit pie filling on top (cherry, peach and blueberry are attractive). Makes about 24.

title: sugar cookies(godmother's special)
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make soft dough.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: peanut butter banana pie
directions: Cut bananas in thin slices on bottom of crust.

title: veggie bars or pizza
directions: Combine dressing mix with cream cheese.
On a large cookie sheet, press rolls, after separating, into pan.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix vegetables; set aside.
Mix other ingredients and spread on bread.
Top with Cheddar cheese; press veggies and cheese down into mixture and cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Recipe can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer, or until done.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Note:
See topping.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: samantha's melting moment cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form dough in food processor or by hand.
Chill dough 1 hour. Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into a 1-inch ball.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Dip a cookie stamp into the granulated sugar and flatten each ball. (If you don't have cookie stamps, you may use the bottom of an etched glass, jar, creamer or sugar bowl.)
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not brown. These are white, melt-in-your-mouth butter cookies.

title: aunt sissie's cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed and spread into pan.
In same bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and flour until well blended. Spoon mixture over brownie batter.
Aunt Sissie always spread hers over the chocolate as a single layer.
You can also swirl with a knife to cause a marbleized effect.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless orange cake
directions: Combine raisins and orange peel; set aside.
In medium bowl cream dry milk with butter.
Add beaten egg.
Add orange juice and beat well.
In another bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add the raisin mixture and stir well.
Stir dry ingredients into orange juice mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven, cool on rack and invert onto serving platter.
Drizzle the sauce over the top of the cake, a little at a time, until the sauce is entirely absorbed. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
The cake improves with age.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lazy day beef stew casserole
directions: Arrange beef and vegetables in 3-quart casserole dish or I use a small roaster pan.
Combine soup and water, pour over meat and vegetables.
Tuck bouillon cubes in casserole at opposite ends of dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Is good served over biscuits.

title: carrot patties
directions: Cook and mash carrots.
Mix in all ingredients.
Refrigerate all day or all night or freeze for later.
Place large heaping tablespoonful in palm of hand.
Pat flour on both sides and form into patty.
Deep-fry (in frying pan) until brown on both sides.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir together pudding and undrained pineapple until completely blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in 1/2 stick butter.
Spread over bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add cooked broccoli spears and cover with rice.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over rice.
Spread Cheez Whiz over top and bake in microwave oven on Medium power for about 15 minutes or until Cheez Whiz is melted and rice is done.

title: almond butter beverage mix
directions: Beat brown sugar, butter, Amaretto, creamer and spices until well blended.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 month.
To serve, spoon 1 tablespoon mixture into mug.
Add 6 ounces hot coffee, wine, cocoa or milk.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with real whipped cream and cinnamon stick.

title: brown rice
directions: Put all ingredients, except rice, in a 2-quart pot with lid and bring to a boil.
Then add rice.
Bring to a second boil. Turn down heat to low.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and water until berries pop.
Turn off fire; add marshmallows and Jell-O.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool some, stirring occasionally.
When Jell-O starts to set, stir in celery, apples and nuts.
Chill.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix up cake mix as box directs; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rhubarb, whipping cream and sugar on top of mix. Bake for at least 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: ham roll-up appetizers
directions: Drain hearts of palm.
Mix cream cheese, onion and lemon juice until creamy.
Spread some cheese mixture on each slice of ham. Place one palm on the short end of each slice of ham and roll up. Place on plate and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
When ready to serve, cut each roll into 1/2-inch pieces and arrange on serving plate.

title: nancy's green bean bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Should make about 6 - 8 bundles.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap bacon around all green beans.
Secure with a toothpick until all are used.
Make a glaze with melted oleo, brown sugar, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Place green bean bundles in 9 X 13 casserole.
Pour glaze over the beans. Bake at 375°
covered for 45 minutes. Then uncover and bake ten to fifteen minutes more.

title: collard greens
directions: Trim and wash greens.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Put in pressure cooker.
Add 1 cup water, salt and oil.
Cook on pressure for 5 minutes.
Cool the cooker and let water boil down. Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and cook 5 more minutes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Season throughout cooking.
Heat on low/medium for 3 hours. Serve with wedge of lemon, if preferred.

title: caramel crispix
directions: You will need 1 paper bag.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then add cinnamon, salt and cloves to flour.
Add to creamed mixture with sour milk.
Add cherries and nuts.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sacher torte(this cake originated in the sacher hotel in vienna)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and lightly flour a deep 8-inch spring-form cake pan.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add the chocolate and mix thoroughly, scraping the bottom of the bowl several times.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time and and mix well after each one.
Stir in flour until no particles show.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry and gently fold them into the batter until no white shows.
Turn the batter into the prepared pan.
Bake on the lower shelf of the oven until the cake shrinks from the sides of the pan and rebounds to the touch when pressed gently in the center or about 1 1/4 hours.
Let the cake stand 10 minutes on a cooling rack before turning out of the pan.
(The cake will shrink slightly on cooling.)
Turn the cake out on the rack.

Turn right side up and let it finish cooling. Stand the rack and cake on waxed paper and spread the top with jam. Pour any desired chocolate icing over the cake and spread it quickly to coat the top and sides.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cook together very slowly in casserole or crock-pot.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Warm milk; add yeast.
When dissolved, add other ingredients and knead well.
Roll into 2-inch balls and put into pan.
Spoon melted butter over top and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Grease 10 x 13-inch layer cake pan.
Put 1/2 of dough in cake pan.
Spread evenly the apple pie mix.
Add remainder of dough.
Pour brown sugar mixture over pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Put each serving in microwave and serve warm.

title: french chocolate truffles
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of double boiler.
Combine butter and confectioners sugar in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Chill until mixture is stiff; shape into 1/2-inch balls for dipping in melted chocolate or 1-inch balls for coating with cocoa, coconut or ground nuts.
Place coated centers on baking sheet to firm. Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.
Yields 24 (1-inch) balls or 48 (1/2-inch) balls.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until cookie dough consistency.
Press into a greased 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster dill crackers(club member:  lee ann mcraney)
directions: Mix oil, dressing and dill. Pour over crackers and toss. Cover overnight before serving.

title: orange stuff
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: 1000 calorie pie
directions: Mix cheese and sugar together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour equal amounts into pie crusts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy coconut cream pie
directions: Combine pudding, milk, egg and sugar; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and coconut.
Cool 5 minutes; stir twice.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with Saran Wrap and chill 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberries, water and sugar to boil.
Cook and cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
You can mold it or just serve with spoon from dish.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Put cornbread mix in large bowl.
Add milk and stir.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Bake in 3 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans at 400° for about 35 minutes or until done.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 1 teaspoon of oil with 14 ounces of almond bark on High for 2 minutes (leave out 1 square of bark) in 2-quart bowl.
Stir.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes more, stirring every 30 seconds until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, peanuts and cereal.
Pour onto a 12-inch, lightly greased pizza pan.
Decorate with cherries.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: soft chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets. Combine flour and baking soda.
Beat butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, walnuts or peanuts and chocolate.
Drop 2 tablespoons batter per cookie onto prepared sheets, spacing 2 inches apart.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes, or until golden brown around edges.
Cool on sheets for about 3 minutes.
Transfer to racks to cool.

title: mommy's chicken ball
directions: Cream the block of cream cheese.
Add the ranch dressing and mix well.
Drain the chicken and separate into small flakes.
Stir chicken into the cream cheese mixture and shape into ball.
Place in the center of a pretty plate and surround with various kinds of crackers.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Stir beef, flour and salt in 2-quart casserole until beef is coated.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium (50%) and microwave until beef is tender, 50 to 60 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Put linguine on to boil.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drain clams and reserve liquid.
Saute garlic for 1 minute.
Add clams, oregano and parsley.
Simmer for 1 minute more.
Add lemon juice and juice from clams.
Simmer for a minute or two; stir in yogurt and remove from heat.
Toss linguine with butter over low heat. Serve with clam sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Place half in dish.
Chop onion, pepper and tomato and add to sweet relish.
Put half over cornbread. Place remainder cornbread in dish.
Mix mayonnaise with remaining onion, tomato and pickle relish and place over the bread.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and 1/2 cup butter.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Put marshmallows over hot cake.
Pat down with a spoon.
Melt peanut butter chips and 1/3 cup white Karo.
Add 3 cups Rice Krispies.
Pour over cake.
Cover cake with 2 cups salted peanuts.
Pat down with a spoon.
Cool and serve.

title: low calorie party salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail thoroughly (save juice).
Pour boiling water over tea bag.
Let stand about 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove tea bag.
Soften gelatin in the lemon juice and dissolve in the hot tea.
Stir in the juice from the fruit cocktail.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Stir in the mint and fruit.
Spoon into individual molds and chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens to serve.

title: peach whip
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1/4-inch pieces. Layer some cake pieces in a 9 x 13 pan. Spread some pie filling over the top. Add another layer of cake pieces and pie filling. Whip jello and chill. Whip cream cheese into lemon whip and chill. Spread over layers. Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip. Serves 15.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar and set aside.
Put hot water, honey, oil and salt in large pan; mix well.
Add yeast.
Make sure mixture is not too hot when adding yeast.
Add flour and knead until soft and elastic.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Knead.
Let rise until double in size.
Work out and put in pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then at 300° for the last 20 minutes or until brown and baked.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Measure 1 cup into bowl.
Add milk, sugar, shortening and well beaten eggs.
Raise yeast in lukewarm water about 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chilled green chili soup
directions: Bring stock and onion to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream in medium bowl. Add green chilies, cumin and garlic.
Stir in stock, heavy cream and salt.
Transfer to blender in batches and process until smooth.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: salsa dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on serving plate.
Chill 1 hour.
Spread salsa over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with grated Longhorn cheese and diced tomatoes.
Cover and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and pepper with corn.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter.
Add milk last.
Place in buttered casserole and bake 1 hour at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup pecans together and mix thoroughly.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Bake at 35 degrees for 40 -45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese (sliced into small pieces), chopped ham and onion.
Form into ball.
Put on a plate and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: You will need 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix flour with other dry ingredients.
Add together with pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add buttermilk and oil; blend well.
Knead on floured surface.
Pat out to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking pan. Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour on 325°.

title: frosted cashew cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a cookie sheet lightly.
Mix baking mix, brown sugar, sour cream, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Stir in cashews.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until no indentation remains when touched. Cool for 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely. Frost with Browned Butter Frosting.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: penuche(candy)
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan real good.
Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan the water, brown sugar and Pet milk; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Boil until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Stir often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Beat until candy is thick and creamy, losing its shine.
Quickly spread in buttered pan.
Cool and cut in about 25 pieces.

title: meatballs in cocktail sauce
directions: Shape ground beef into 1 inch balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and basil and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add meatballs, cover and refrigerate.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion and cheese well.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with corn flakes, then pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and long rice
directions: Fry garlic and ginger in oil (chicken fat may be used) until brown.
Take out garlic and ginger, add chicken and fry until slightly browned.
Add water and cook until chicken is tender (about 2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Add long rice and seasonings.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Beat cake mix, margarine and 4 eggs together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Watch closely, easy to burn.

title: pizza primavera
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 14-inch round pizza pan or a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; set aside.

title: cherry foursome parfait
directions: Whip cream with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in sour cream. Alternate layers of cherry filling and whipped cream mixture in parfait or sherbet glasses beginning with a red layer and ending with a white one.
Top each with a single cherry.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 8 Servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to butter mixture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: glazed lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is baking, mix 4 tablespoons lemon juice and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Punch holes in warm cake.
Pour glaze over cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and let stand for 1 day for best taste.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Boil meat, 3 teaspoons salt, pepper, green pepper and onion in enough water to cover until tender. Drain well.
Set broth aside. Put both meat and vegetables through coarsest blade of meat chopper. Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup, salt, Tabasco sauce and chili powder.
Mix well.

title: heavenly cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers, 4 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat firmly against bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: yogurt cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs with butter until blended.
Press firmly onto bottom of well-greased 8-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: little norwegian birds
directions: Place thin slice of onion and 2 to 3 slices of carrots on each slice of meat.
Dust with salt, pepper and flour mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks or thread.
Brown on all sides in melted butter.
When all pieces are brown, cover with water.
Add a few bay leaves and 1/4 teaspoon allspice.
Simmer 15 minutes. Make a paste of flour and water; pour over meat and simmer about 45 minutes more for flavorful gravy.
Watch carefully after 30 minutes to be sure gravy doesn't cook away.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and zucchini; add egg and mix well. Mix dry ingredients, then add to cream mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Stir through.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie
directions: About 3 hours ahead or early in day:
Prepare pie crust with fluted edge; refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat pumpkin with next 10 ingredients until well mixed.
Place pie plate on oven rack; pour pumpkin mixture into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn oven control to 350° and bake 35 minutes more or until filling is set.
Cool. Serve topped with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken or beef cutlets
directions: Slice chicken or beef and pound to desired thickness.
Dip in egg, then in seasoned bread crumbs. Place in baking dish with oil or Pam. Bake and turn cutlets and add liquid from can of black olives and can of mushrooms.
Bake about 1/2 hour, then add mushrooms and olives. Bake 1/2 hour. Serve with baked or mashed potatoes and salad and vegetable for a complete meal.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Add oats and nuts. Mix well. Make rolls in waxed paper and chill.
Slice 1/2-inch thick. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in baked pie crust.
In a medium sauce pan combine sugar, flour, jello, and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, on medium heat until mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over strawberries in pie crust.
Let cool and frost with whipped topping.

title: gnocchi
directions: Wash potatoes; leave skin on.
Boil in approximately 1/2 inch of water.
Peel while hot, then mash potatoes; let cool.
Then add 4 cups of flour, grated cheese, salt and eggs.
Knead together until large dough ball is formed.
Roll segments into long strips. Cut strips into gnocchi size (1/4 inch).
Place pieces into floured pan.
Leave in cool place until ready to cook. Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes (stir one time).
Serve in sauce.

title: pina colada flip
directions: Mix cream of coconut and pineapple juice.
Add ice cream, then club soda.
Makes one small punch bowl.
Delicious!

title: quick skillet 57
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening; drain off excess fat. Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Stir.
Bring to boil. Simmer on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, covered, stirring constantly.

title: okra cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour ingredients into a well-greased 9-inch pan.
Add the smidge of grease on top of the bread and bake at 500° until bread turns golden brown.
Very delicious!!

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dip chicken cutlets in egg and milk, then in flour.
Put margarine in frying pan and brown cutlets in pan on both sides. Place cutlets in baking dish.
In frying pan, add in margarine, 1 can chicken broth, mushrooms (minus the juice), salt and pepper to taste and a pinch of parsley.
Stir.
Add 3/4 cup of red wine; stir again.
Bring to boil; simmer.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and 1 cup of hot water; simmer until thick.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and simmer in 2 quarts of water for 2 hours.
Remove, debone and dice.
Add vegetables; simmer, uncovered, until beans and potatoes are tender.
Add cornstarch to make thickening.

title: wimpy's feet toast
directions: Place bread on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Also place oleo and garlic
in oven in covered Pyrex dish or measuring cup.
By doing so, your oleo is ready when your toast is.
Dribble oleo on toast.
Sprinkle well with Parmesan cheese, pizza seasoning or Italian seasoning and lightly with cayenne pepper, if desired.
Let cool a few minutes.
Enjoy warm or store in airtight container.
Great munchies!
Also great with salads!

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until blended.
Mix in other ingredients except nuts. Chill for several hours.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: whole meal dinner(crock-pot)
directions: Put raw hamburger in the bottom of the crock-pot.
Put diced potatoes, cut carrots and onions on top of burger.
Pour soup over and crock during the day.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cut up peppers, onion and mushrooms into small pieces. Saute until almost cooked and put into sauce. Bake sausage for 30 minutes at 325° or until almost done. Cut sausage into bite size pieces. Put into sauce. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box.
Crumble 1/2 of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling and sprinkle pecans and half pineapple.
Spread 1 box of Cool Whip over this.
Proceed with layering remaining ingredients.
To serve, use regular punch bowl dipper or large spoon.
Serves 36.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat on stove on medium heat or heat in coffee percolator.
Serve hot.

title: rotel tomato dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Melt cheese.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and sausage.
Mix well.

title: caramels
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until very thick (230°).
Add butter. Stir.
Add cream gradually so mixture doesn't stop boiling.
Cook until firm ball (242°), stirring constantly.
Add salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into well greased sheet pan.
When cool, cut into small squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: coconut cream pies
directions: Heat 9 cups of milk to boiling point.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to hot milk; stir until thick.
Add 1/2 pound of butter; stir well.
Cool pudding until chilled, then add 4 teaspoons coconut flavoring and 1 1/2 cups coconut flakes.
Put in 4 baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and 1 1/2 cups white sugar.
Beat again until stiff, then put on top of pies and brown in oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thickened and pour into pie shell.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 10 x 11-inch pan (bigger than pie dish).

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and crushed red pepper.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Cover with pizza sauce. Sprinkle onion, green pepper and pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella and return to oven.
Remove when cheese has melted.
Serve hot with crackers, bread sticks or garlic bread.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine and blend well the sugar, soup, vinegar, oil, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add carrots, green pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: crusty casserole loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in electric mixer bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, softened margarine and 3 cups flour.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium speed until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Scrape beaters and beat in the rest of the flour by hand.
Cover and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until more than doubled, about 45 minutes.
Stir down.
Beat vigorously about half a minute.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix together and bring to a boil the butter, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or foil to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut into bite size chunks and place in a 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Dot pats of butter over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste and cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Velveeta slices over potatoes and add Ranch dressing.
Return to oven and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Bring margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil; stir. Let boil for 3 minutes. Take off heat and add oats and peanut butter. Stir until peanut butter is dissolved. Pour onto cookie sheet; let cool. Then cut.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine the sugar and corn syrup in 3 quart microwave casserole and cook for 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add the peanuts and continue to cook another 3 to 4 minutes.
Next, add the butter and vanilla; continue to cook for an additional minute.
Finally, add the soda and gently stir until mixture is light and foamy. Pour and spread quickly on a greased, flexible baking sheet.
Cool for 1/2 hour and break into small pieces to finish cooling.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt and sour cream.
Cook over medium heat to a soft ball stage.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool without stirring.
Beat.
Add nuts and pour into greased 8-inch square pan.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine in a large mixer bowl the flour, salt, nonfat dry milk and dry yeast.
Heat in saucepan over low heat until warm the water, cooking oil and honey.
Pour warm (not hot) liquid over flour mixture.
Blend at low speed for 1 minute, medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: 3-bean bake
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Put in casserole and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In frying pan, melt butter or fat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, broth and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Add chicken; heat through.
Serve over biscuits.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; rinse and drain.
Add dressing and seasoning.
Add chopped onion, chopped tomatoes, cucumber, celery, ripe olives or whatever veggies are fresh.
Toss all; refrigerate overnight.
Makes 20 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3 1/2 qt. slow cooker and cook on low (200°) for 6-8 hours.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: lite poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat in water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan before removing.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix all together very well.
This mixture should be pretty soupy.
Bake for about 5 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven or stuff into a turkey.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out 1 biscuit.
Place 1 spoon of apples on biscuit.
Roll out another biscuit and place on top of apples.
Pinch ends together.
Do this with all the biscuits and place in dish.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, cinnamon and 7-up.
Bring to a boil and then pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender, then add soup and cheese. Cook until cheese melts.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and drain fat.
In a large bowl, mix hamburger meat, chopped lettuce, tomato, beans, cheese and onion.
Crumble up Doritos chips and stir into mixture.
Pour Catalina dressing over salad and mix before serving to taste or serve separately to apply individually.

title: mashed potato pizza dough
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.
Put on toppings, whatever you like.

title: crab soup
directions: Put crab meat in double boiler, add butter, onions, and pepper. Cook for a few minutes.
Heat milk and add to crab mixture.
Stir and add cream and Lea & Perrins.
Add flour and sherry, stirring all together well.
Cook over a low flame for about 30 minutes. Turn into a tureen.
Makes 8 servings.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour and sugar together. Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and water and stir until elastic-like strands form.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
To shape, place dough on well floured surface, smooth and shape.
Place in greased pan, cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin cups.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fill muffins 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 regular sized or 36 mini muffins.

title: microwave stuffed hamburger balls
directions: Form 6 to 8 patties.
Spoon stuffing onto one pattie.
Take second pattie and form a ball around stuffing.
Repeat for remainder of patties.
Mix soups and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Place hamburger balls into casserole dish.
Pour soup mix over them and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Place in oven at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Can also be placed in microwave for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 or 4 large balls.

title: patra's icebox torte
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crumbs.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Melt together marshmallows and milk until melted.
Cool.
When cooled through, add the fruit and Cool Whip.
Fold together; put on crust.
Sprinkle with reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in one stick of butter.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss and serve with the following dressing.

title: smells of christmas
directions: Combine ingredients into a mesh bag or cheesecloth and secure with a string (NOT ribbon).
Place in ziplock plastic bag; refrigerate until ready to use.
Place 1 quart water into a saucepan; remove from plastic bag and place in water.
Simmer all day, adding water as needed.
Can be used for several days.

title: pie crust
directions: Work shortening into flour and salt mixture with pastry blender or fingers.
Add water until flour is moistened.
Gather dough together with fingers so it cleans bowl.
Press into a ball and roll between two pieces of waxed paper.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese, almond extract and sugar. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir dry ingredients into butter mixture and mix until
just combined.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in crisp rice cereal coarsely crushed. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with half a cherry. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: unflappable chicken
directions: You will need 1 large 14 x 20-inch oven cooking bag.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine the cookies (crumbled) and margarine.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Gradually add creme de menthe to marshmallow cream, mixing until well blended.
Fold in heavy cream.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with topping.
Freeze.
Serve in small pieces; very rich.
Let defrost slightly before serving.
Equally good if Kahlua is used instead of creme de menthe.

title: delight!
directions: Melt margarine.
Cut it into the flour.
Stir in pecans. Flatten out crust mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: rolled and stuffed flank steak
directions: Lay steak out on counter and sprinkle with Adolph's instant tenderizer and salt and pepper.
Then cut a diagonal pattern on both sides of the meat.
Make any stuffing recipe you like and spread it evenly on one side of the meat.
Roll meat and stuffing like a jelly roll and tie securely with kitchen string or fasten with skewers.
Cover meat and top of pan with aluminum foil.

title: mexican brunch puff
directions: Place
all
ingredients
in
a	greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes until puffed and golden.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix onion and cabbage.
Add sugar and celery seed; mix and set aside.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, salad oil, salt and dry mustard; pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
May be kept in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish and add the following topping.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and salt.
Add egg, vanilla and chocolate.
Beat until blended.
Add soda and flour until just mixed.
Roll into 1 teaspoon balls and roll in sugar and coat. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: golden anniversary punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients
together, except for the 7-Up.
This makes 1 1/2 gallons without the 7-Up.
At serving time, add 7-Up according to your taste.
Float a decorative ice ring in the punch bowl and you will have a beautiful and good tasting punch for any occasion.

title: orange salad(low calorie)
directions: Drain orange slices and pineapple. Blend cottage cheese and jello. Use jello directions on package. Add orange slices and pineapple. Mix well; fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hula cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Arrange noodles, meat mixture and cheese in layers in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
I add some Cheddar cheese along with other cheese to the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand a while before cutting.

title: strawberry pie 1
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy and add milk, lemon juice and flavoring.
Chill 3 hours and add strawberries and glaze.

title: vinegar candy
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until mixture is brittle when dropped in cold water (270°).
Pour onto buttered plates.
Mark into squares while warm or roll into small balls.
This is an excellent hard candy.
An old time favorite.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Place rice in greased baking dish or pan; spread.
Add beaten eggs, margarine, sugar, salt, vanilla, milk and raisins.
Stir in pan with fork.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
May add about 1 cup more milk if it seems too dry.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients and 2 cups of water and simmer for 1 hour.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter at high speed in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating at high speed until light and fluffy. Stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts by hand until well blended.
Pour batter into greased Bundt or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours and remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: cajun catfish with rice
directions: Combine water, rice, salt and all 3 peppers in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Melt
margarine
in pan.
Mix all ingredients together, adding melted
margarine	last.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: clam and oyster soup
directions: Clean and pick over oysters.
Using 1/3 cup cold water, reserve liquor and add oysters, slightly chopped.
Clean and pick over clams.
Reserve liquor and add to hard part of clams, finely chopped.
Put aside soft part of clams.
Heat slowly to boiling point the clams and oysters with liquid from broth.
Strain through cheesecloth. Scald milk with onion, mace, parsley and bay leaf.
Remove seasonings and add milk to stock. Thicken with butter and flour, cooked together.
Add soft part of clams and cook 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Boil eggplant until tender; peel and mash well.
Add all ingredients to eggplant.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter. Drop by spoonful in hot oil.
Brown; drain on paper.
Serve hot.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in skillet.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and spices.
Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and sides of a slightly greased baking dish.
Top with half of meat mixture. Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange remaining tortillas over cheese.
Top with remaining meat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with Cheddar cheese and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: my favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni noodles until tender.
While noodles are boiling, mix beaten eggs and milk until well blended.
Add salt and pepper to milk and egg mixture.
Mix together noodles and milk mixture, adding cream cheese and 3/4 of the Cheddar cheese.
(Save other 1/4 for topping.)
Mix well and finish by sprinkling remaining Cheddar cheese on top of macaroni.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then raise temperature to 400° to brown cheese on top, approximately 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon, sifted together.
Mix well.
Stir in diced or chopped apples, nuts (walnuts or pecans) and vanilla.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix apricot, French dressing, onion soup mix and chicken in bowl.
Marinate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve over rice and enjoy.

title: preacher's shrimp pasta bruscato
directions: Sauce:
Heat olive oil in pan and saute garlic, bell pepper and onion until wilted.
Add fennel seed, oregano and margarine. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, 1/2 whole and 1/2 chopped, in order to distribute the flavor.
Stir gently until shrimp turn pink (approximately 10 minutes).
Add heavy cream, salt and pepper to taste and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick (pudding consistency), stirring constantly.
Chill.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover the first 4 ingredients with 1 tray of ice cubes and cold water.
Place in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight. Drain cucumbers well.
Mix mixture of remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Bring to a boil, but do not cook.
Stir gently so they are all the same color.
Seal in hot, sterile jars.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs and sugar slightly.
Stir in margarine, flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes till firm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and shortening. Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly. Add buttermilk; stir to just moisten.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden ranch linguini with chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except the cheese) in saucepan.
Toss well.
Heat through and sprinkle with cheese.

title: calvin's no. 1 bologna sandwich
directions: Take the Miracle Whip, spread some over the bread, then put both slices of bologna on each bread slice.
Then add your tomato and cheese.
Then sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk gradually. Cook and stir until sauce begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks; add to sauce.
(Add a little hot sauce to eggs and beat before adding to sauce.
Cook another minute to thicken.)
Add salt and nutmeg. Add all to tuna in baking dish.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add celery, mushrooms or lemon juice to tuna, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy scratch biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Add shortening.
Mix with a fork, then add milk.
Stir until mixture follows fork.
Scrape out onto floured surface.
Flour all sides and pat into circle the thickness you desire.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Biscuits will be light and fluffy.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Wash berries.
Boil sugar, water and salt for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook over low heat until berries become soft (about 10 minutes).
Rub through a sieve and chill.
Pour into tray and freeze about 2 hours.
Remove, stir and serve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer
carrots, onions and peppers.
Add sparingly salt and pepper.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Keep airtight for 12 hours.

title: easy cheese fondue
directions: Toss cheese with cornstarch to coat.
Place in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir from bottom as cheese begins to melt.
When softened and smooth, gradually add wine, stirring vigorously after each addition, until wine is absorbed.
After all wine is added and fondue is creamy, stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour into chafing dish, fondue pot or other flameproof serving container.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, both strawberry Jell-O boxes, nuts and coconut and chill.
Form with fingers into the shape of strawberries and roll in red colored sugar and top with green colored sugar.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Excellent as a garnish or to add color to a dessert.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown
and
drain hamburger.
Place Velveeta, Mozzarella and Cheddar
cheese
(shredded)
in
4-quart crock-pot on low. Dice onion and green pepper.
Drain tomatoes and green chillies and dice finely.
Place
hamburger,
onion, green pepper, tomatoes and green chillies
in
crock-pot
with the cheese and add garlic salt to taste.
Let
cook
for
about 1/4 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve hot over tortilla chips.

title: cafe au lait mousse
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar, coffee and salt in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup milk.
Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining 1 cup of milk.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 4-cup mold or individual serving dishes.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer cauliflower, broccoli and carrots.
Cube a small package Velveeta cheese and place between each layer.
Crush 1 stack Ritz crackers and layer on top.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and add eggs.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with icing of 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar and juice of one lemon.

title: cheese roll
directions: Sprinkle with paprika.
Roll in parsley flakes and chopped nuts.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add dates, nuts and candy to flour to coat.
Add coconut.
Combine both mixtures.
Makes stiff dough that should be mixed with hands.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Combine orange juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over hot cake.
Let stand overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put dough into bowl with sugar.
Shake until covered.
Layer in a 9-inch round pan.
Melt margarine and add to remaining sugar. Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend butter, Crisco, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave until hot.
Stir chili into Cheez Whiz and heat.
Add Durkee onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain off pineapple juice.
Mix pineapple, oranges, lemon juice and condensed milk, then add Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust. Chill.

title: naomi's seven layer casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and layer ingredients in dish.
Potatoes on the bottom and soup on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat 1-inch of oil in a skillet.
Soften the tortilla in the hot oil for a few seconds.
Drain it on a paper towel and lay it flat on a plate or baking sheet.
Cover the tortilla with refried beans.
Decorate it with tomatoes, onions, olives and peppers. Top with cheese and salsa.
Sprinkle with the olive oil.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 375°
oven.
Serves 4.

title: squash relish
directions: Sterilize pint/quart jars and lids. (Recipe makes about 3-4 quart jars.)

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Add marshmallow cream and beat until stiff but not dry.
Spoon over pie.
Put in 350° oven until peaks begin to brown.
Lower oven heat to 250° and brown evenly.
Turn off oven and let pie set until oven cools.

title: bread pudding, chez helene's
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs. Add milk, evaporated milk, nutmeg, vanilla and bread.
Add raisins and stir to mix. Pour into a deep greased casserole and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Stir after first hour.
Serve warm with hard sauce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Roll pizza crust over a lightly greased cookie sheet and try to make it cover the pan.
Bake for 8-10 minutes.
Let it cool.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mash out one biscuit at a time.
Spoon on tomato sauce.
Put on lots of pepperoni.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Use baking directions on label of biscuits.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Combine the cake mix with water. Melt butter and add to mix, then add 1 egg and then pecans. Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13).

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Right before you serve, cut up the avocados and mix all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.

title: st. joseph's cream puffs
directions: For Puffs:
Combine water and margarine in a deep saucepan. Bring to a boil; cook until margarine melts.

Quickly stir in flour and salt. Beat until dough forms a ball in center of pan. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Beat in orange rind. Mixture will be very stiff. Drop mixture by tablespoon onto a baking sheet, which has been greased.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until puffs are firm and crusty (prick each puff with a fork to release steam).
Leave in oven an additional 5 minutes. Remove from oven; cool.

title: grammy's banana pudding
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 C. milk at medium speed; blend well.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat 1 minute on low.

title: pistachio salad or dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients, but fold Cool Whip in last.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix together the tomatoes, soup and cheese.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring halfway through and after it's done.
Serve with tortilla chips and enjoy.
Great if kept in crock-pot.

title: chili burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes, cheese and buns.
Shape mixture into 8 patties, each about 1/2-inch thick.
Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Broil patties with tops about 3 inches from heat until medium doneness, 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Place 1 tomato slice on each patty; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Broil just until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.
Serve patties in buns.
Makes 8 sandwiches; 460 calories per sandwich.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Blend first five ingredients.
Beat at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Cool for minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to make a thin batter.
Spread over the cake while it is still warm.

title: chicken soup
directions: Use big soup kettle.
Put chicken in pot and fill pot with water 3/4 full.
Add onion and celery.
Cover and boil until chicken is tender or pulls away from bone.
Add carrots last 1/2 hour.
When carrots are tender, bone chicken and put chicken back in soup.
Add egg noodles or rice as desired.

title: magic bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt the margarine. Add the graham cracker crumbs and form a crust on the bottom of the dish. Next, add the milk, then in layers, add the coconut, semi-sweet chocolate butterscotch drops and pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: quick dark chocolate fudge
directions: Spray an 8-inch square pan with cooking spray.
In a 2-quart saucepan, stir corn syrup and milk.
Add chocolate, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium-low heat, until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar with wooden spoon. Beat until smooth and glossy.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 25 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: roll-out christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients together; blend, then chill.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter shapes.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Decorate.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased bundt pan. Bake 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: campsight fish
directions: Place fillet on 12 x 6-inch sheet of aluminum foil.
Melt butter and pour it on top of fish.
Wrap fish in foil and place in an open fire.
Let cook for 5 to 10 minutes and then turn it over for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into walnut-sized balls.
Stir cinnamon and sugar together; roll each ball into mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: strawberries and sour cream
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Add pineapple; stir.
When partially set (almost immediately), put half the jello in a mold or clear bowl.
Let set.
Spread sour cream over it and pour remaining jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Chill.

title: lemon or vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk, then add lemon or vanilla flavoring.
Add flour a little at a time.
Beat until creamy.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start cooking cake in a cool oven.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Wash and drain spaghetti.
Sprinkle in seasoning and add vegetables.
Pour in 1 cup dressing; add to taste.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Brown slightly.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in skillet and cover with sauce.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and butter to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Drop quickly by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let set up.

title: caramel souffle
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups sugar in a skillet.
Heat until brown over medium heat.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole or Bundt pan.
Coat the sides and bottom.
Rub with butter.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add 1 pound of sugar gradually, beating constantly.
The remaining sugar, put in a skillet and brown.
Add a little water and cook until the syrup forms a thread.
Pour into the egg whites at medium speed.
Return to high speed and beat for 12 minutes. Pour in buttered container and bake at 300° in a hot water bath for 1 hour or until firm, but light.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Place 2 or 3 c. milk in a saucepan.
Heat to scald.
Pour half of it into beaten eggs, stir well, and pour back into pan. Bring back to scalding.
Remove from heat and cool.
When egg mixture has cooled.
Add all ingredients, mix thoroughly, and place in ice cream freezer.
Follow manufacturers directions.

title: pie meringue stabilizer
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thickened.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add cooled mixture.
Beat once more.
Spread over pie, making sure meringue touches crust.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter and pour over cereal.
Mix cereal until coated.
Put powdered sugar in a brown paper bag.
Pour in cereal; fold over top.
Shake until coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: lemon-apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together mixing 1 egg at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove onto plate and while still warm, drizzle glaze on top and sides.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Add enough water to vinegar to make 1/2 cup.
Add eggs and sugar.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add this to a pint of Miracle Whip.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that you have dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove.

title: fruit pizza
directions: One of two ways to arrange: Using a pizza pan, spread sugar cookie dough (like pizza dough) and bake, being careful not to brown edges before center is done.
Fruit will be arranged in a circular pattern and slices will be triangular like pizza slices.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, jello, lemon extract and apricot nectar in a large bowl.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in greased and floured tube pan.
Mix the powdered sugar and lemon juice and pour over cake while it is still hot.

title: strawberry-pretzel dessert
directions: *Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: ralph's chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green peppers. Add balance of ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb crunch (2)
directions: Place above ingredients in a 9 inch baking dish and let stand.
Mix together the topping.

title: italian goulash
directions: In skillet, brown onion, ground beef and green pepper. Add tomatoes, vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar, garlic pepper, and salt.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown the pork in large frying pan in oil.
Add water, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Mix in bowl the juice from pineapple, green pepper, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add mixture to pork with chunk pineapple and bring to a boil.
Serve over hot rice.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Add part of the cheese and mix.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
(I use a candy thermometer but it is not necessary.)
Take off heat and add margarine.
Let completely dissolve and quickly add peanut butter, stirring mixture.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: stuffed shells deluxe
directions: Cook and drain macaroni shells.
Set aside.
Combine cheeses, eggs, bread crumbs and parsley.
Stuff each cooled shell with cheese mixture. Pour layer of spaghetti sauce in a large baking dish. Arrange stuffed shells, seam side down, over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk and eggs; blend well.
Mix in sugar and spices, again blending well.
Stir in crumbs.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp in a bowl.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until fluffy and smooth.
Add chili sauce.
Add mayonnaise gradually.
Beat in lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Last, add shrimp and beat until all ingredients are well mixed. May be made day before.

title: mini pecan delights
directions: Cream 1 cup margarine and cream cheese. Blend in flour.

Chill dough 1 hour. Shape into 48 balls. Press dough into mini ungreased muffin tins; shape to form little pie shells. Beat together eggs, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine and vanilla. Stir in pecans. Fill each shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set. Cool and remove from pans.

title: jalapeno noodles and cheese
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put soup and cut-up cheese in pan to melt.
When cheese is fully melted, pour mixture over noodles and add green beans.
You may substitute 1 can drained white tuna for green beans.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
All ingredients should be cut up fine.
Blend well and pour into a floured and greased tube pan.
Bake in a 275° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baby carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/3 of vegetables in casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 of cheese.
Layer twice more.
Bring broth to boil.
Pour over layers.
Bake 45 minutes or until top browns.
If vegetables begin to dry out add a small amount more of broth.

title: vegetables
directions: Meal #1:
Bake in oven as you would any potato.

title: coconut angel cookies(weight watchers)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until begins to brown, 7 to 10 minutes. Makes about 40 cookies.

title: john david's green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix green beans, soup and onion rings together.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good with steak and green salad.
Also good to take to church socials.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Chop broccoli.
Combine broccoli with grated cheese and spread mixture evenly in pie crust.
Beat eggs lightly with milk and seasoning.
Pour over cheese and broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until lightly brown and completely set.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the oil, eggs and baby food.
Mix well, but do not use a mixer.
Add the chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: liver and onions
directions: Brown liver in cooking oil until both sides are slightly brown.
Add envelope of dry soup to liver.
Add 1 cup water.
Then put chopped onions on top of liver.
Simmer for about 30 minutes and then serve.
Don't overheat.
Liver will be tough.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Put ice cream sandwiches in bottom of 9 x 13 glass dish. Spread Cool Whip on top. Squeeze chocolate "Magic Shell" on top of Cool Whip. Put into freezer for 4 hours. Cut into squares, then serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onions until beef is brown and drain.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: burritos
directions: Fry hamburger, add beans and any other ingredients.
Cook until beans are hot.
Make burritos using tortillas stuffed with beans and meat mixture.
Add shredded cheese as desired.
Smother with green chilies.

title: white trash
directions: Use a large bowl to mix last 6 ingredients.
Melt almond bark in microwave 1 1/2 minutes in glass bowl on Full power.
Stir and repeat with a wooden spoon.
Pour over all the dry ingredients. Stir real good.
Pour this on waxed paper.
Flatten by hand.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease shallow 2-quart casserole.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine 3 cups milk and syrup; heat just to boiling over medium heat.
Add butter.
In small bowl, combine cornmeal, ginger and nutmeg.
Gradually stir into hot milk in saucepan.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring, until thickened (about 10 minutes).
Stir in raisins and spoon into casserole dish.
Pour in remaining milk; do not stir.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours, until milk is absorbed and top is golden brown.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half crosswise.
Mix together bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons oil.
Spread mixture on the cut side of tomatoes.
Arrange in an oiled shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining olive oil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan caramel cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserve 10 caramels. In saucepan, combine rest of caramels and 1/2 cup half and half. Cook and stir until melted.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Spread over prepared crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour, cool.
Cook reserved caramels with 3 tablespoons half and half until melted.
Spread over cake.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Chill thoroughly.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine macaroni, cheese, milk, salt, onion powder, mustard and pepper.
Cook, covered, with lid at Medium for 9 to 10 minutes; stir twice during that time.
Cook, uncovered, at Medium 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, Karo and milk.
Let the mixture come to a boil, then turn to low and cook 5 minutes, stirring all the time. Take off stove and add butter and vanilla. Add nuts.
Beat until ready to pour on plate.

title: our favorite oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in baking pan.
Add the vanilla, vinegar, shortening and cold water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Toss together lettuce, onion, celery and cucumbers.
Next, layer in a 9 x 9 x 3-inch dish the lettuce mixture, thawed peas, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over the whole salad.
Then place sliced green pepper rings on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, butter, eggs, flour, sugar and milk; put in casserole.
Mix pecans, coconut, brown sugar and butter. Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 24 hours, turning once.
Drain and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: boston baked haddock or flounder
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with butter or margarine.
Spread over fillets.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Sprinkle on small shrimp.
Spread on can of cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop onions very fine. Chop dried beef. Combine onions and beef with cream cheese. Add garlic salt. Mix well. Form a ball. Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt. Put in pretty bowl with a lid. Refrigerate. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In a small
bowl, combine 3/4 cup salsa and sour cream. Spread chips
on
baking
sheet.
