Layer salsa mixture, chicken and cheese on chips. Broil until cheese melts.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Cabbage and olives may be added to mixture when it is set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together sausage, egg and bread crumbs.
Form into balls. Melt butter in a frying pan and brown meatballs.
While browning, mix together in a separate bowl chile sauce, garlic salt, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour over meatballs and let simmer. You may pour butter off meatballs before adding sauce mixture if you wish.

title: award winning chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix soups, broth and milk together.
Mix margarine and dressing together.
Layer chicken and dressing in casserole dish. Pour soup mixture in each layer. End with soup mix.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 30 minutes until heated through.
Enjoy.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs; add fruit cocktail, sugar, flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nut mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pecan roll
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, kneading in last of sugar gradually.
Shape into eight rolls, 1-inch in diameter.
Put in freezer overnight.
Melt caramels in top of metal double boiler. Remove from heat but keep over hot water.
Dip marshmallows.
Roll into caramel to cover, then roll in nuts.
Cool covered in dry place.

title: zippy butter potatoes
directions: Melt butter 45 seconds to 1 minute in microwave.
Add garlic salt, paprika and cheese.
Dip sides of potatoes in mix.
Cook in microwave 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake uncovered and turn after first 5 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins in a greased Bundt pan.
Cut dough into 10 pieces.
Roll each piece of dough in melted butter and a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place pieces in a pan and cover with cloth for about 3 hours or until dough doubles in size, then bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli spoon bread
directions: Place flowerets in a saucepan with 1 inch boiling, salted water.
Cover; cook 10 to 12 minutes until tender.
Drain; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine corn meal, flour and salt. Gradually add water, bringing to a boil, stirring until thickened. Stir in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Remove seeds and chop peppers.
Add vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Put through cheesecloth or jelly bag.
Add sugar.
Use Certo as directed.
Boil 1 minute.
Add green coloring.
Put in hot jars.
Makes 6 half-pints.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Wash peaches.
Add to the syrup and boil gently until fruit is fork-tender.
Pack peaches in hot sterilized jars and fill with pickling liquid.
Serve as relish with meats.

title: christopher's favorite sausage and cheese loaf
directions: Thaw and roll out dough into 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Layer cooked sausage, thawed broccoli and cheese. Seal bread dough around ingredients.
Flip seam side down.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes on baking sheet.

title: never fail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan pie(cincinnati milacron recipe)
directions: Mix sugar and salt. Stir in butter and eggs. Blend in syrup and vanilla.
Put pecans in shell and pour in filling. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until pie is set.

title: peanut butter balls(candy)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Dip into melted milk chocolate.
Set until firm.

title: best ever pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Add rice.
Mix orange juice and soup; pour over chops.
Cover with tight lid and let simmer until rice is done and pork chops are tender.
(May also place the browned chops in a baking dish and finish the cooking process in oven at 325°.)
Real, real good!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Spray bottoms only of two 8 1/2 X 4 1/2 inch loaf pans with non-stick cooking spray.
Combine four, salt, and baking soda in small bowl.
In a mixing bowl, combine shortening, sugar, mashed bananas, eggs, nuts, and vanilla extract, beating until well blended.
Add flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60-70 minutes or until toothpick inserted pulls out clean.
Remove pan from oven.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: one and only casserole
directions: Crumble ground meat in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with rice and soup mix.
Pour water over mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir with fork.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Wash and remove seeds from jalapeno peppers.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Boil 1 minute.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli, broth, water, onion, celery, salt and pepper in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Pour half of vegetable mixture in food processor or blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Repeat.
Return to saucepan; heat until boiling.
Shake flour and 1 cup milk in tightly covered container until smooth. Gradually stir into hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining milk and nutmeg.
Heat on low heat until hot.
Garnish with sour cream or heavy cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dressing for summer fruit plate
directions: Combine juice and grated rind of fruits to egg and sugar that have been beaten.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute; remove and cool.
Arrange variety of cut up fruits on platter or on small, individual plates. Drizzle dressing on top.
May sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring liquids to a boil.
Put 2 clove garlic and 1 head of fresh dill or 1
tablespoon
dill seed to each quart.
Fill jars with pickles, then
cover
with
boiling
water, then set jars in hot water
and
place
on
burner until pickles change colors.

title: sweet and sour onion
directions: Mix vinegar, butter and brown sugar.
Pour over onions.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: country style steak in the pot
directions: Cut steak into serving portions.
Coat with four.
Brown on both sides in shortening in skillet.
Place in crock pot. Sprinkle onion over steak.
Add soup and water to pan drippings in skillet; mix well.
Pour over steak.
Cook on low for 6 hours or until steak is tender.

title: white nut loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and egg; stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add nuts and stir only until nuts are blended into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given and pour into greased and floured 12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Let stand in baking pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Chill.

title: casserole rabbit and sausage
directions: Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Skim fat before making gravy.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Season tomatoes with onion, salt and pepper.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, alternate tomatoes and toast cubes, having toast for top layer.
Pour butter over and bake at 375° until heated, about 20 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together eggs, oil, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix next 4 ingredients together.
Mix 3/4 of the dry mixture into the wet mixture.
Mix the remaining 1/4 dry ingredients with the berries and fold them in.
Fold them from the outside of bowl until all flour is mixed well.
It should not look wet but don't use so much flour that it's dry.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, oil, corn, chilies, cheese and onion; blend well. Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moist. Bake in a 10-inch skillet at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pickled squash
directions: Dissolve salt and enough water to cover vegetables.
Soak for 2 hours.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Combine sugar, celery seed and vinegar in large pan; bring to boil.
Add squash, onion and peppers.
Bring to boil.
Place in sterilized jars.
Cover vegetables with liquid.
Place sterilized lids and bands on jars. Close tightly.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Fix noodles according to directions.
Drain water.
Mix butter with noodles.
Add cheese and Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Tear chicken into pieces and mix into noodle mixture.
Pour into baking pan.

title: frosted pimiento cheese rolls
directions: Stir the onion into the water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat together the margarine, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix in the onion, pimiento and parsley.
Spread one side of each bread slice with cheese mixture.
(Soften cheese mixture in microwave a bit to make it easier to spread.)
Roll each bread slice like a jelly roll. Place close together (sides touching) on baking sheets with sides. Spread tops with remaining cheese mixture.
Just before serving, bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 100 to 120.

title: hot peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half
and take out seeds.
Pack in jars. Heat the mixture and pour
in filled jars.
Boil in water bath for 25 minutes.
Make 10 pints.

title: sin
directions: Note:
This is the recipe that Lynne uses for the bazaar every year.
"Pine Grove is the only church in the area that can sell Sin."

title: impossible bacon lettuce and tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Layer bacon and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except lettuce
and
tomatoes,
until smooth (15 seconds in a blender). Pour
into
plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean,
30 to
minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Garnish with
lettuce
and tomatoes and, if desired, bacon and mayonnaise.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken until done and debone.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on package.
Add chicken while cooking.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables the last 5 minutes.
When done, add soy sauce.
Stir and serve.

title: crab stuffed chicken
directions: Place 1 chicken piece, bone side up, between waxed paper. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Accent.
Pound chicken lightly and set aside.

title: plum or apricot dumplings
directions: Bake potatoes.
Peel while hot and puree.
Make dough with potatoes, butter, flour, sugar and eggs.
Pit the fruit and stew in wine with cloves over low heat, just until boiling.
Remove fruit carefully from wine and cool.
Make dough into two rolls and cut into one-inch slices.
Place one piece of fruit on one piece of dough, covering fruit completely.
Cook in simmering, salted water over medium flame.
Be careful not to boil, about 10 minutes. Carefully remove.
Brown bread crumbs in a little butter and mix with cinnamon; sprinkle over dumplings.
Can also be served with vanilla sauce.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour half the batter into a greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inches).
Sprinkle the cheese over the top and add remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in ovenware bowl or casserole. Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Fry onions in bacon fat until tender but not brown.
Mix sugar and mustard.
Add onions in frying pan. Add beaten eggs and vinegar; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, bacon and egg slices.
Mix lightly.
Heat in a 250° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle parsley on top.

title: pita squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Slit pita bread and spread with cheese mixture.
Cut into squares or triangles.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.
Put in freezer bags and keep frozen
until you wish to bake them.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Pour in yeast.
Add shortening and mix.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Form into ball.
Place in oiled bowl. Cover and put in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: nutty bean bread
directions: Place raisins in small bowl, cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 10 minutes, drain.
In a medium bowl combine flour, sugars, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Add beans, oil, eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into a 9 X 5 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes, remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: marshmallow eggs(for easter)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, then dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into bowl; beat until very thick.
Pour into prepared flour molds.
Let set 1 hour, then dip in chocolate.

title: mojarras o truchas al mojo de ajo(fish in garlic)
directions: Wash fish.
Peel garlic and put in blender with juice from the lemons, salt and pepper.
Liquefy and pour over the fish.
Marinate one hour.
Meanwhile, cut tomato, avocado and onion.
Season with salt and pepper and toss to have ready to serve with fish.
Fry fish and serve.
Serves 6.

title: tenderloin-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water; rinse and drain. Slowly brown tenderloin on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: mexican cheese roll
directions: Spread Velveeta between wax paper with a rolling pin.
Spread on cream cheese.
Sprinkle on black olives, green chilies and chopped onions.
Roll up.
Fix cracks while you roll.
Garnish and serve with Ritz crackers.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: johnny cake(corn bread)
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg, milk and oil to dry mixture and blend well.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until slightly brown on top.
Serve hot or cold with butter, honey or preserves.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, margarine, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter until very creamy.
Add the vanilla, Karo and soda. Stir into creamed mix the rolled oats, M&M's and chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned (not very dark; this will keep them chewy).
Makes about 12 dozen, but you have to be a "Cookie Monster" to eat them all!

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onions until tender; add soup, sour cream, milk and seasonings.
Heat until warm and smooth.
Add chicken and heat. Layer tortillas and chicken mixture in 3-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pumpkin marble cheesecake
directions: Combine pecans and margarine; press onto bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt together chocolate, marshmallows and milk.
Cool thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: fruit bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs; add milk and flour alternately.
Add fruits and nuts.
Chill several hours, then bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Do all in a blender.
Store in a covered container in the freezer.
When using, fill a glass about half full of slush and the rest with ginger ale.

title: ozark apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs in mixer bowl for 1 minute. Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together. Add to creamed mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Add water, vanilla, apples and pecans, stirring to mix. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45
to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cut into squares. Spoon warm Caramel Sauce over each serving.

title: lumber jack stew
directions: Combine vegetables and sausage with water.
Cook until tender. Add mushroom soup and simmer 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stir-fry american style
directions: In small bowl, combine beef or chicken with soy sauce, sherry and ginger.
Let stand 15 to 30 minutes.
Preheat 1 tablespoon oil in wok, uncovered at medium-high, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add reserved mushroom liquid, cover and steam 4 minutes.
Remove carrots.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok. Add cauliflower and pea pods or peas; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Push up to the side.
Add onions and mushrooms; stir-fry for 2 minutes. Push up to the side.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Add half of the meat with marinade; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Push up to the side.
Repeat with remaining meat.
Add carrots.
Combine water, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir into meat mixture and cook until thickened.
Reduce heat to low for serving.
Serve with rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: onion slim dip
directions: Mix skim milk and drained cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Mix eggs; then add other ingredients.
Place one vanilla wafer in each paper cupcake liner; place liners in muffin pans.
Pour mixture on top of each wafer (3/4 full).
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.
Remove paper cup liners and freeze.
Freezes well.

title: no-bake fudge
directions: Blend together cocoa, butter and cheese.
Mix well and add sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and shape into long rolls.
Put in waxed paper and let set.
When ready to serve, slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Makes 18 to 24 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Clean and steam diced squash.
Drain. Combine and mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach frozen yogurt
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a saucepan and let stand for 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and salt, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in yogurt, vanilla and peaches.
Cover and chill.
Pour mixture into can of a 4-quart freezer.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, margarine and mashed bananas.
Add baking soda, flour, salt, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Line pan with aluminum foil.
Spoon 1 teaspoon at a time on foil and place each spoonful 3-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool just enough to handle them.
Remove from pan by lifting foil and pulling cookie from foil.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
The butter makes them crispy like Grandma Hofen made.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Place beef in a Dutch oven.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour over beef.
Cook until beef will shred with a fork.
Serve.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Put butter in cold heavy skillet.
Melt slowly; add eggs, sugar, salt and dates.
Cook slow, stirring constantly and mashing dates, for 15 minutes, until very thick.
Pour over the Rice Krispies and mix well.
Cool; form into small balls.
Makes 35.

title: easy quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients (not frothy) and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before cutting.
Freezes nicely!

title: cherry salad
directions: In pretty bowl, alternate layers of cherry pie filling, sliced bananas, marshmallows and coconut, saving some cherry pie filling to drizzle over top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and roll into 1-inch balls. Bake on a Pam-sprayed cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. These may be frozen.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use same size cans of fruit cocktail, pineapple chunks and Mandarin oranges.
Drain well.
Add same size can of coconut. Also, same amount of miniature marshmallows and nuts.
Add sour cream to mix.
This will last several days in the refrigerator.

title: 10 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes or a little longer.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Grease 13 X 9 pan.
Combine cake mix (less 1 c.) with 1/2 c. melted butter and 1 egg, press into pan.
Combine pumpkin, spices, brown sugar, 2 eggs, milk, 1/4 c. melted butter.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Mix reserved cake mix with 1/4 c. sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce(similar to kroths)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour slowly.
Cool completely.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook 15 to 30 minutes.
For hot sauce, add 1/2 tablespoon red pepper. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in glass jar or plastic container.
Use 2 teaspoons in cup of hot water.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Fit 16 muffin cups with paper liners or grease each cup well.
Set aside.
Combine the melted butter, eggs, molasses, pumpkin puree and orange juice in a bowl. Mix until well blended.
Combine the flour and whole wheat flour in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir with a whisk to combine.
Gradually stir the liquid ingredients into the flour mixture, mixing until just combined.
Fold in the walnuts and cranberries.
Spoon the batter into the muffin cups.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until completely cooked through.
Serve warm with unsalted butter. Freezes well after being completely cooled.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar. Set aside.
Put Crisco and sugar together and cream. Add slightly beaten egg yolks. Add flavorings.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add salt and soda and sift again.
Add milk alternately with flour, then fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat 4 to 7 minutes or until peaks form.
Remove from water and add flavoring, as desired.

title: paul's black-on-black vegetarian chili(makes 10 servings)
directions: Soak beans according to package directions overnight or "quick soak."
Drain and rinse.
Combine the beans in a heavy pot with the black olives and the crushed tomatoes, including any liquid that they come packed in.
Add water to the level of the beans, but not to cover.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes well. In pan, melt oleo, add soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix with potatoes and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (or large casserole).
Do not cover.
Bake at 420° for 45 minutes or 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; stir in baking powder.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour 1 quart of peaches over top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Break bread into small pieces.
Mix mustard in a little milk so it blends well.
Crumble the fried sausage.
Mix in all ingredients and put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: rainy day soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in frying pan until beef is brown; drain.
In large boiler, combine beef, onion and peeled and diced potatoes; boil for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Enjoy with cornbread on a cool rainy day.

title: rolls
directions: Pour into 2 regular or 4 small loaf pans which have been greased and sugared (spray with Pam and sprinkle with sugar). Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Test for doneness.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Wrap well and store in refrigerator.
You can add nuts, dates, raisins, bananas or almost anything you like.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook yams in boiling salted water; peel and cut in halves lengthwise.
Place pieces in greased baking dish.
Cook honey, sugar, butter or margarine and hot water together for 5 minutes. Pour syrup over yams and bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) about 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until cooked.
Let cool.
Cut open.
Scoop out potatoes.
Mix with milk, cheese, butter and bacon pieces until fluffy.
Re-fill hollowed out skins and re-bake until slightly brown.

title: baked sesame chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt margarine; set aside.
Blend eggs, water, soy sauce and pepper in a shallow dish.
Dip each chicken breast into flour, then egg mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and place in baking dish. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Serves 6.

title: glazed pork loin
directions: Rub flour and seasonings
into roast.
Place roast, fat side up, in a shallow
roasting pan (no water).	Roast, uncovered, at 325° until meat thermometer registers 185°.
Allow 35 to 40 minutes per pound.	About
one hour before end of roasting time, mix applesauce,
sugar
and
spices
and spread over roast. Return to oven until done.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put in bottom of jars: 1/8 teaspoon alum, 2 or 3 small pieces of garlic and dill or dill seed.
Wash cucumbers and place in jars.
Mix vinegar, water, turmeric and salt.
Pour this over cucumbers and seal.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick-and-easy mashed potatoes
directions: Combine water and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in potato flakes.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cover potatoes and keep warm.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove tops and seeds.
Place upright in 2-quart micro-proof casserole on High (maximum power) for 2 minutes. Drain water.
Let peppers stand while preparing filling.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add zucchini.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour, depending on size pans.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: In a 2-quart greased casserole, combine hamburger, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, macaroni, water and cheese.
Sprinkle some cheese on top and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Combine pinto beans, onions, garlic, water and tomato sauce. Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add lentils.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add water as needed.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Take chicken and pound each piece.
Then place on grill, grill almost done and cut.
Grill on low, then pour 1 tablespoon A.1. sauce on each piece of chicken.
Then place mushrooms on top of sauce and put cheese on top of that.
Cut off grill, close top, let cheese melt and then serve.

title: hello dollies
directions: Grease 12 x 12-inch square pan.
Melt butter; add to crumbs and press in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and pecans over this.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake in 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Cream the butter or margarine.
Add sugar slowly and beat until light.
Beat in eggs; sift the flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 2 round layer pans or Bundt pan.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Pour into pans. Bake oblong 60 to 65 minutes or layers 50 to 55 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables or small shrimp.

title: cajun corn souffle
directions: Separate eggs and beat.
Combine egg yellows, oil, corn, pimentos, jalapenos and corn bread mix.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole for the last 3 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Chop onions and brown in butter.
Add tomatoes and 3 cups water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and paprika.
Boil until rice is soft.
Insert knife at the stem of each pepper; remove the top, seed and core.
Parboil the peppers about 6 minutes.
Mix hamburg and 1 teaspoon salt and add enough of the rice mixture to fill the peppers.
Replace tops.
Pour remainder of the rice into a buttered baking dish.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 cup of water.
Set the peppers in the rice and dot with butter.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 30 minutes or until done.
Add more water if necessary.

title: banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well and chill that for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream, then the bananas.
Line sides and bottom of 3 1/2-quart bowl with cake slices.
Spoon pudding mixture into prepared bowl.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with banana slices. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 package of yeast in 2 cups warm milk.
Add oil, sugar, egg and flour.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, 3/4 full.
Place in warm place.
Let rise about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake in 325° oven until done.
Remove. Brush tops with butter.

title: pineapple roll-ups
directions: Wrap 1/2 ounce of ham or turkey around each pineapple spear. Fasten with toothpicks.
Combine catsup, grape spread, mustard and pineapple juice.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of sauce over each pineapple spear.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes. Use any remaining sauce for dripping.
Yield:
10 roll-ups. Serving size:
2 roll-ups.

title: mom's 4 quart ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients except egg whites. Beat whites until stiff and add last.

title: zucchini bread 1
directions: Blend together eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, salt and zucchini. Sift flour and add to mixture and stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in a sprayed baking dish.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: becker's cottage cheese pie
directions: In blender, combine hot water and Jell-O.
Add lemon juice and cottage cheese; blend well.
Remove from blender and place in bowl.
Add Cool Whip and beat at low speed.
Place in pie plate and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Garnish with kiwi or any fruit in season.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and pork lightly.
Add celery and onions.
Stir and brown, add other ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots and walnuts to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus tips; place in casserole dish.
Put mushroom soup (as it comes from can ) on tips.
Sprinkle lightly with cracker crumbs.
Put dabs of butter on cracker crumbs.
Cover mixture with cheese.
Cook in moderate oven about 15 minutes or until heated through and through.
Serve from casserole.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dutch baby pancake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in blender.
Coat 6-inch cast iron skillet with 2 tablespoons melted margarine (may use a nonstick frypan with handle covered with foil).
Pour egg mixture into pan. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Serve hot sprinkled
with confectioners sugar or with maple syrup.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: broc-a-noodle-stew
directions: Melt butter and oil in large pot.
Add onions, celery and carrots.
Saute until soft.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes and juice and vegetable broth.
Simmer until cauliflower is cooked.
Add zucchini, cook until barely soft.
Add noodles, cook 10 more minutes.
Serve hot topped with Parmesan cheese or sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy quick chicken
directions: In a plastic bag mix together dry ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in butter or orange juice.
Drop chicken 2 to 3 pieces at a time into dry ingredients.
Shake to coat.
Place on a foil lined baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Cook meat in butter until done.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles and meat sauce in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given.
Pour into a greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° about 30 minutes.
More red cayenne pepper can be added if you want it hotter to your taste.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Stew chicken and remove from bones; cut in bite-size pieces. Cook spaghetti in salted water until tender.
Chop the pepper, celery and onion; saute in margarine 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup and chicken broth; stir until smooth.
Combine chicken, eggs and spaghetti in greased casserole.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my sister's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in pan.
Cover with foil and bake for an hour at 425°.
Remove foil for last 15 minutes to allow loaf to brown.

title: apple snaps(sugar-free jell-o gelatin salad)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in applesauce and cinnamon.
Pour into dessert dishes. Chill.
Soft set in 30 minutes.
Yields 5 servings, each under 50 calories.
Ready in 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter English muffins on both sides and put in 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
Fry sausage and drain.
Pour over muffins.
Mix eggs and sour cream.
Beat well and pour over muffins and sausage.
Put cheese and then chilies on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in covered pan.
Reheats well in microwave.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine in pot 2 cups sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, pinch of salt, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Boil for one minute.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter, 3 cups oatmeal and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Mix well.
Add raisins at this point if wanted.
Quickly drop spoonful on waxed paper and let cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix lemon juice and buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° until it is firm in the middle.
Makes 2 pies.

title: red hot sausage dip
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz and peppers.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in warm milk (stir constantly) over low heat, until desired thickness.
Serve over a hot buttered biscuit with a tall glass of milk.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce and cornstarch; let stand 20 minutes.
Prepare vegetables according to package directions. Stir-fry chicken and onion 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken is white.
Add prepared vegetables.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; cook until thickened.
Stir in cashews.

title: meaty nacho dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook until meat is brown. Drain.
Melt cheese; combine with cooked meat.
Stir in sour cream.
Can be served with chips.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water; add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.

Add sausage and corn; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink. Remove with a slotted spoon onto a serving platter.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Yields 12 servings.
Great meal for a crowd, quick and easy!

title: saute carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots and cook until almost tender (but not completely done); drain.
In skillet add butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Melt and stir together.
Add drained carrots and saute for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from burning or sticking.

title: butter crumb broccoli
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; add parsley, onion, dill, salt and broccoli.
Cover; cook over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes until tender.
Remove cover; add pimiento and croutons.
Toss to cover and serve immediately.
Serves 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: michigan cherry dipping sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.
Serve with crispy chicken bites.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels (not too fine) and mix with melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake; cool completely.

title: almost heaven dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in that order and serve with or without chips.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Follow directions on box.
Peel and dice cucumber, onion and hard-boiled eggs.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Chill and serve on crisp bed of lettuce.

title: peanut butter pie(very rich, restaurant style)
directions: Mix all well.
Pour into graham cracker (9 or 10-inch) pie shell.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw 10 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix everything together. Pour into ovenproof dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly on top.
Serve with garlic rounds or bagel chips.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crushed crackers and melted butter. Pat firmly against the bottom and sides of a deep 9-inch pan. Blend cream cheese in a mixing bowl until soft and creamy. Add sour cream and mix well. Beat eggs and add sugar and vanilla. Stir well and add to cream cheese mixture. Blend and pour into cracker crust. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven and cool.

title: hot brown sandwich
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and cook until clear.
Add flour and blend to make a smooth paste.
Add milk, salt and red pepper.
Stir and cook until thick and smooth.
Stir in cheese, eggs and remaining tablespoon margarine.
Continue to cook, stirring, until mixture almost reaches boiling point, but do not let it boil.
Remove from heat. Fry bacon crisp (and crumble if desired).
To assemble, toast eight slices of bread, cut four in half diagonally.
On four oven-proof plates, arrange toast.
Lay sliced chicken or turkey over toast. Cover with sauce, then add bacon.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika (optional).
Place under broiler until sauce begins to bubble.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Sift
the flour and spices together in small bowl, then blend Crisco,
sugar and eggs in a big bowl.
Blend flour into persimmons,
dates,
nuts
and
raisins.
Blend
together
all ingredients,
adding
baking
soda	last.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then turn to 350° and bake for 45 minutes longer.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Saute shallots in oil or water until soft.
Add cornstarch to milk and stir until dissolved.
Pour over shallots, stirring constantly.
Add spinach and nutmeg.
Continue cooking over medium heat until thickened and heated through.
Garnish with pine nuts before serving.

title: pickled sweet peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut into strips.
Place peppers into pint jars.
Mix spice, vinegar and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over peppers.
Seal.
Put in water bath about 15 minutes.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: california vegetable dish
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine with cheese.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish and add vegetables.
Pour cheese sauce over. Melt the other stick margarine and add crackers.
Sprinkle this over the top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients except cheese and barbecue sauce. Shape into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
After baking 45 minutes, add 3 slices of cheese over top and pour 1 cup of barbecue sauce over the top.

title: the $250 cookie
directions: Cream the butter with the white and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, blending well. Stir in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Then add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts. Roll (or scoop with ice cream scoop) into balls (about the size of golf balls). Place 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes. Makes about 112 cookies.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in large pot and rinse several times.
Add sausage and ham; cook, covered, to a creamy consistency for about 3 to 4 hours.
Add seasonings, onions and Ro-Tel tomatoes during last hour of cooking.
Serve over rice.
Serves 15.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and put into pot.
Add vinegar and salt.
Boil for 1 minute.
Put other seasonings and oil in another dish. Drain mushrooms and put into oil; refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, salt, pepper, butter and onion over pork chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring to a rolling boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables; toss and chill.
(This is better if you allow the vegetables to marinate overnight.)

title: carrot casserole
directions: Pre-boil sliced raw carrots for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in butter; set aside.
Prepare white sauce in the usual way.
Layer carrots, which have been mixed with onion and white sauce, alternately with chunks of Velveeta.
Sprinkle with buttered cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in hot oil.
When tender, add beef and brown.
Then add all other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: hash browns dish
directions: Combine all ingredients (except corn flakes) in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add beaten egg, salt and flour.
Fry in lightly greased skillet on medium until golden.
Makes 7 to 8 cakes.

title: plum and apple crumble
directions: Note:
Feel free to substitute 6 cups of nay cut-up fruit for the plums and apples.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish with butter. Clean crabmeat and put in bowl.
Mix in eggs, one at a time, then mayonnaise and onions; should be loose and creamy.
Place mixture in buttered baking dish.
Pour 1/2 melted butter on top.
Arrange crushed saltines on top.
Add shredded cheese as top layer.
Pour melted butter on top.
Place in oven and bake.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown onion in small amount of bacon drippings.
Add hamburger meat and rest of seasonings and tomato sauce; mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add beans.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: orange-glazed sugar snap peas
directions: Place peas with 1 tablespoon of water in a microwave dish. Cover and cook on high for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain liquid.
In a small cup, combine brown sugar, orange juice and margarine.
Microwave on high for 30 seconds; drizzle over peas and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Boil 3 1/2 to 4 minutes. Have oatmeal, cocoa and coconut mixed together and ready to add to cooked ingredients as soon as they finish boiling.
Then drop mixture by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Allow to set.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix
all
and top with bacon.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Blend in salt, vanilla and flour.
Mixture is stiff.
Pinch off small piece of dough; shape in balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at ???° for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water.
Set aside and cool (do not refrigerate).
Mix together cream cheese and sugar; add cooled jello and mix until smooth.
Beat chilled evaporated milk until thick; add vanilla.
Combine the 2 mixtures together and fold until smooth.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine soda and hot water.
Cream sugar and butter; then add beaten eggs.
Add melted chocolate, then add milk and flour alternately.
Beat.
Then add soda/water mixture and vanilla. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
This is my great-grandma's recipe.

title: mushroom pork chops with potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops and cook for 15 minutes, add a little bit of water and soup.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.

title: holly's easy chicken parmesan
directions: Cook chicken patties until done in oven.
Pour spaghetti sauce over patties and cover with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly.

title: pumpkin apple pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, salt, water and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling.
Add sliced apples and cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Spread mixture in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Combine egg, pumpkin, sugar, salt, spice and evaporated milk.
Mix well and carefully pour over apple mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: baked opossum with sweet potatoes
directions: Boil opossum until tender.
Bake sweet potatoes until tender. Place meat in a roasting pan, season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and thyme.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake further until browned.

title: cheesy salmon casserole
directions: Rinse turkey.
Butter all sides (inside and out) of a paper grocery bag.
You can either rub butter all over the turkey and salt it and sprinkle paprika on it or you can melt the butter with the salt and paprika on it and pour the mixture all over the turkey.
Either way is fine.
Place the turkey in the bag and fold the end over so the heat will stay in.
Make sure you place the bag in a pan so the juice will stay in the pan (not on your oven floor).
Bake on lower rack of oven at 350°.
Bake 15 minutes per every pound of turkey.
(You might bake 15 minutes more.)

title: apricot tea
directions: Dissolve tea in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add rest of water with lemonade and apricot nectar.
Add ginger ale.

title: cherry swirl cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour pan.
In large bowl, blend first four ingredients until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Reserve 1 cup cherry filling for topping.
Spoon remaining cherry filling over batter; gently swirl through batter to marbleize.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Spread reserved cherry filling over cake.
Top with whipped topping.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: truffles
directions: In medium bowl combine ingredients and cream until smooth. Roll into walnut size balls.
Into a 1/2 cup of finely ground almonds roll each truffle.
Chill.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift baking powder, flour and salt.
Measure melted shortening.
Add sugar; stir until well mixed.
Let cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden chicken casserole
directions: Combine the soups, water & salt. Mix well. In a greased 13 X 9 baking dish, layer a third of the soup mixture, half of the tater tots, half of the vegetables, and half of the chicken. Repeat layers. Top with remaining soup mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover & bake at 350 degrees for 60-70 minutes or until bubbly. Uncover & bake another 5-10 minutes longer or until browned & heated through.
6-8 servings.

title: four star chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat on low until near boiling, but do not boil.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
May use small crock-pot.

title: chocolate chip marble drop cookies
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, oil, 3 tablespoons water, egg and chocolate chips.
Transfer a small amount to a small bowl.
Add one tablespoon water and the small package of chocolate from the cake mix.
Drop small amount from each bowl on ungreased cookie sheet (or slightly mix two mixtures together for swirl effect). Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Can also mix in pecan pieces.

title: honey mustard dipping sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Gently boil squash (whole) until tender.
Let cool slightly, then slice lengthwise and scoop out pulp into bowl.
Cook sausage and chopped onion; drain off excess oils.
Add to pulp of squash, then add stuffing mix.

title: five bean salad
directions: Bring to a full boil sugar, vinegar and oil.
Cool.
Drain and wash the beans.
Combine beans, celery, green pepper and pimentos. Add dressing and mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9-inch pie pan with crust for 40 to 45 minutes in an 375° oven.

title: pear cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over pears and let set until juicy.
Stir in other ingredients until well blended.
Pour in 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May double and make in regular cake pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar or make a glaze.

title: dilly casserole bread(1 round loaf)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and dry yeast.
In saucepan, heat cottage cheese, water and butter until mixture is warm.
Add egg and warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at lowest speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour,

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add juice from pineapple and Coca-Cola.
Congeal slightly.
Add softened cream cheese to cut up cherries, nuts and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix again. Refrigerate another 24 hours.
Shape into 5 loaves.
Place loaves on pan so grease can drain away.
Bake at 150° for 4 hours.
Turn over and bake 4 more hours.

title: mother maxine headen's lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Mix well the milk, lemonade and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla to egg whites.
Bake pie shell until brown.
Pour filling into baked pie shell. Spread meringue on top of pie and let brown in moderate oven.

title: jello carrot salad
directions: Prepare jello.
Grind or grate carrots and apple.
Cut orange in small pieces.
Add all ingredients to jello.
Coconut or pecans are also good in this recipe.
Use other fruit if you wish.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Place butter in bottom of pan and melt in oven. Mix all ingredients, except fruit or juice, in a bowl. Pour this mixture over batter, then pour fruit or juice over this and bake until brown.

title: carolina coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage (coarse or fine, to your liking).
Add pepper and onion; mix together.
Mix sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Add vinegar and oil.
Bring to a boil; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage.
Cool to room temperature; cover and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date and nut balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and dates in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and nuts.
Cool to touch (don't wait too long). Shape into bite size balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Do not refrigerate; they get too hard.

title: toffee 'n fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt to margarine mixture; blend at low speed until the dough forms, about 1 minute.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Stir in nuts and half of crushed toffee bars.
Press in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crushed toffee bars.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 25 bars.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and blueberries.
Add to juice, hot boiling water according to Jell-O package.
Add Jell-O and set aside 2 cups of mixture and leave at room temperature.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger meat and sausage; drain. In
a large
skillet
combine the two meats and pour in Prego sauce. Let
simmer.
Drain
noodles
and
place in a layer of noodles
in long,
rectangular pan to cover bottom.
Then put half
of
the meat on top of noodles and then 1 bag of cheese. Repeat layer of noodles, meat and second bag of cheese.
Place in a 350° oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: morgan's delight(tortilla casserole)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Combine with all other ingredients except cheese.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake as directed. Let cool.
Spread cream cheese mix over top.
Sprinkle cream cheese, veggies and onions over the top. Cut into 1 x 1-inch squares and serve.

title: layered potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Layer in onions, ground beef, potatoes and corn.
Mix soup(s) with equal amounts of water and pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until potatoes are soft.
Good when topped with seasoned salt, cheese or ketchup.

title: tart cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice.
Combine jello and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Chill until partly set.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry and celery.
Pour into mold. Chill until firm.

title: opera creams
directions: Place in large kettle.
Stir frequently to 258°.
Pour on cold marble slab.
Do not scrape kettle.
Cool completely.
Add vanilla and walnuts.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beets.
Add beets.
Simmer until tender, 1/2 hour or so.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
Place in large skillet and add oil (enough to cover bottom of pan).
Add sugar on top as it is cooking (may need to add more).
Let cook on medium for approximately 25-30 minutes or less till potatoes are soft and turning brown.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into 2 well buttered pans.
(You do not need a crust for this pie.)
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top mixture with 1 package of Ritz crackers, crushed fine and mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve while hot.

title: cheese-grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 1 cup of boiling water, with salt, until slightly thickened.
Beat into margarine and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add enough milk to eggs to measure 1 cup liquid.
Add egg mixture to grits.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: channing's gooey s'more squares
directions: Cover bottom of 8-inch square microwavable dish with 9 of the graham cracker squares.
Spread chocolate morsels evenly over the graham crackers.
Spread marshmallows evenly over chocolate morsels.
Put the rest of the graham crackers on top of the marshmallows.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute onions.
In large bowl mix soup, Cheez Whiz, onion and rice.
Fold in broccoli.
Put in glass pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans (after soaking overnight) with water and add ham bone or ham hock, onions, bell pepper, garlic, red pepper and Tabasco.
Cook slowly for several hours until tender.
Add salt AFTER beans are cooked.
Add cooked sausage and serve over hot rice.

title: dream whip topping(butter glaze)
directions: Boil for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup coconut.
Spread over cake while icing is hot.
Great on Ugly Duckling Cake.

title: deer stew
directions: Cut deer meat into small chunks.
Put deer meat and water into pressure cooker and cook for 30 minutes.
Wash potatoes and carrots and cut into chunks.
Add to deer meat.
Cut onion into small pieces and add to mixture.
Add tomato sauce and mixed vegetables to cooker.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to season. Pressure cook for another 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scandinavian cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.	Add
egg
yolk	and mix. Stir flour in and make little
balls.
Roll in beaten egg white and chopped nuts.
Spoon
onto	cookie	sheet.	Insert	finger print on top.
Bake 5 minutes
and
press
again.
Bake 15 minutes. Remove from oven and
fill indentation with jelly.	Bake at 350°. Makes 45 cookies.
Do not grease cookie sheet.

title: maple nut sponge
directions: Add hot milk to slightly beaten egg yolks and cook over boiling water until the mixture thickens slightly. Remove from heat. Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes. Add to first mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add maple syrup and salt. Cool and when mixture begins to congeal, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into serving glasses and chill.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Mix 30 seconds.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gumbo-sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion well.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, stirring after each addition.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Cool and cut shrimp into small pieces.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
Add shrimp, then add Tabasco.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: papaya salad
directions: Squeeze the juice from tamarind that has been soaked in water. In a bowl, mix all ingredients except kale or lettuce until well blended.
Spoon the papaya salad on a serving platter.
Arrange kale or lettuce on one side of the platter.
To serve, spoon papaya salad on kale or lettuce leaf and wrap taco style.
Eat with fingers.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In blender, puree broccoli, chicken broth and seasonings; set aside.
Blend flour in melted butter; add milk and cheese.
Stir until thickened.
Add broccoli; puree and warm thoroughly.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix the cans of soup on bottom of a casserole.
Add the raw rice
and
mushrooms.
Layer
pieces
of
chicken on top. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top of chicken and add 1/2 can of
water. Cover
and
bake
for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: In glass bowl, thinly slice cucumber and onion.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: baked cranberry pudding
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar and egg yolks.
Add whipping cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, orange peel, baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and salt.
Stir in chopped cranberries and completely coat them.
Add brown sugar mixture and butter; mix well (batter will be very stiff).
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add remaining cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: sticky chicken wings
directions: Bake wings at 400° for 45 minutes.
Heat soy sauce and sugars over medium heat until the sugars are dissolved.
Pour over wings. Turn oven down to 300° and bake slowly for another 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn them once in a while and keep them in a single layer. Use as either an appetizer or main course.

title: sesame pork ribs(slow-cooker)
directions: In large bowl combine first 9 ingredients.
Add ribs and turn to coat.
Place onion in slow cooker.
Arrange ribs on top.
Cover and cook on low 5-6 hours.
Place ribs on serving platter. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and green onions.
Serves 6.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cut bread 1/2 through the length.
Then cut into serving slices.
Put into foil.
Spread cheese mixture between each slice.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Wonderful.

title: smoked fish chowder
directions: Saut onions and celery with butter. Add flour to thicken (about 5 minutes).
Add clam juice; simmer.
Add cubed potatoes and remaining spices and whitefish.
Salt to taste.
Before serving, add 1 quart heavy cream for every gallon of soup prepared.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix lightly peas, grated cheese, diced hard-boiled eggs, cream of mushroom soup, cracker crumbs and nuts.
Place about half in greased casserole.
Put layer of asparagus tips.
Put rest of mixture over asparagus, then top with remaining asparagus, grated cheese and pimiento for color.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: play dough
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add cooking oil and food coloring. Add dry ingredients.
Mix and knead until smooth.
Store in a plastic bag or container, preferably in the refrigerator.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion lightly in shortening.
Combine with beef gravy, beef, carrots and peas into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon potatoes on top.
Bake in very hot 450° oven about 25 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix together well.
Freezes well if made ahead of time.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch (loaf) pan or 2-quart round casserole dish.
Mix sugar, mashed bananas, oil and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Bake until pick comes out clean.)
Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Grease
and flour pan, pour into greased pan.
Let cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: our favorite vegetarian pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet or pizza pan. Cook as directed on package.
Cool.
Spread with Ranch dressing. Top with broccoli, cauliflower and onions that have been chopped small.
Top with cheese.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cheese, milk, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add sugar, beating until frosting is smooth.

title: easy delicious cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on the box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in the cake with a fork.
Cook pineapple with sugar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cake.
Cook vanilla pudding according to directions and pour over pineapple.
Let cool.
Spread with Cool Whip, then sprinkle coconut on top.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat 1 (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Combine jello, hot water and strawberries.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then add marshmallows.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Cover with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts over Cool Whip.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, add baking soda and let stand while preparing rest of cake.
Cream oleo, sugar, egg and milk. Add date mixture, flour, 1/2 cup nuts, 1/2 cup butterscotch chips. Pour into greased 14 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: chicken and artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice mixes according to package directions, omitting butter.
Cool.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade and slice.
Add artichokes, pepper, olives, onion and chicken to rice. Blend together artichoke marinade, mayonnaise and curry powder. Add to rice salad, toss lightly.
Chill.
Chill at least 4 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Blend in sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend dry ingredients together and add to batter.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces, set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken into batter and fry in hot vegetable oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry crumb muffins
directions: Combine ingredients with fork until crumbly.

title: grandma's chocolate crinkles(cookies)
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by dipping, then leveling.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture. Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoon into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar; shape into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and add flour. Add broth, milk and water. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Stir in salt, rice, chicken and vegetables. Pour into a greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all other ingredients stirring well.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: banana split cheesecake dessert
directions: Set aside filling and strawberry topping packets from cheesecake mixes. Place contents of the crust mix packets in a bowl; add butter and sugar. Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine milk and contents of filling packets. Beat on low speed until blended. Beat on high for 3 minutes or until slightly thickened. Spread over crust. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix in
13	x 9-inch dish for crust, 2 cups crushed graham crackers,
cup	powdered sugar and 1 stick melted margarine.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Boil noodles in water until tender.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain well.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish noodles, ground beef, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Continue layering ingredients twice more.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Flour steak and brown in hot oil.
Place steak in long casserole dish.
Separate onion into rings and place on top of steak.
Top with tomatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meats.
Cover with foil and cook on 250° for 2 1/2 hours. Uncover the last 15 minutes to cook down to a thick sauce.
Has a delicious smoked flavor!

title: chow mein
directions: Stir-fry celery and onions in oil in large skillet for 3 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomato and consomme.
Stir in remaining seasonings.
Thicken with cornstarch, if desired.

title: chess cake
directions: Add melted margarine and 1 egg to cake mix.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and remaining 3 eggs together and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over pork chops. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: candy cookies
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over low heat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients into melted chocolate.
Chill mixture well.
Shape into marble size balls and roll in chopped walnuts.
Store covered in fridge.

title: jalapeno cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape in ball and roll in nuts.

title: tortillas
directions: Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add shortening and mix well.
Add water and mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured surfaces and knead, 50 strokes.
Divide dough into 12 equal parts and form balls.
Cover with a cloth and let rise 15 minutes.
Roll pour into greased inch circles.
Cook on a low heat, skillet ungreased, until done.
Wrap in towel to keep warm.

title: miracle cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Whip 2 minutes at low speed with mixer or by hand (300 strokes).
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes one 10-inch square or two 8-inch round layers.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix baking powder, flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine melted butter, sugars and vanilla.
Mix together.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Fold in oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Scoop out walnut size balls of dough onto a sprayed or nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool on cookie sheet 5 minutes.
Remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Mix together and spread on top of biscuit dough.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Thaw spinach; crush garlic.
Add garlic to spinach and cook in microwave about 3 minutes.
Combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Layer with sauce and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Heat chocolate and butter over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla. Add hot water, 1 teaspoon at a time, until glaze is at desired consistency.
May be used with cake or ice cream.

title: quinch fruit dip
directions: In a small serving bowl, stir together yogurt, cream cheese, sugar, lemon peel and juice.
Cover Fruit Dip with plastic wrap; refrigerate.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Prepare
cake
according to package directions and bake in
a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine undrained pineapple and sugar. Heat until
mixture
comes
to a boil.
Boil about 2 minutes. When cake is done, remove from oven and puncture all over with a fork.
Pour pineapple over hot cake.
Let cake cool.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and cut up chicken.
Mix together vegetables, soup, milk and chicken pieces.
Spread the two pie crusts in bottom and on sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chicken mixture into crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll out crescent dough on top of pie and bake 10 minutes more or until golden brown on top.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix well 4 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour.
Take out of oven, pour glaze over cake and let set in pan 30 minutes before turning out.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend together flour, brown sugar, crackers, soda and salt. Cut in margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with pie filling and top with remaining crumb mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies(even people who hate fruitcake love these.)
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and other ingredients, mixing well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: veal paprika
directions: Cook the bacon and remove and drain on paper.
Brown the veal and onion until golden in bacon fat.
Add the bacon, chicken broth, garlic, paprika and salt.
Cover and simmer until veal is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix the flour with sour cream and add to the veal and cook until it thickens.

title: steak on a stick
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut into 36 (1 1/2-inch) cubes.
Set aside.
Combine remainder of ingredients, except toasted rolls, in a large, shallow dish.
Add steak.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain steak, reserving marinade.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: dandy donuts
directions: Mix vanilla, milk, water, eggs, sugar, and oil in large bowl. Sift in rest of ingredients. Mix well. If needed add a little more flour to make dough so you can handle it. It should be soft. Fry in shortening or lard at 350 degrees until cooked through. Approximately a minute on each side.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, or 2 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 9-inch loaf 55 to 65 minutes, 8 1/2-inch loaves 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Saute onion in large frying pan.
Add sliced zucchini and cook until tender.
Drain excess juice and arrange tomatoes on top of zucchini.
Top with cheese.
Reduce heat and cover until cheese melts.
Eat and enjoy.

title: pigspagoot
directions: Slightly brown pork in shortening; salt very lightly.
Saute celery in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add to browned pork; mix in tomatoes.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add cooked spaghetti, mushrooms, lima beans and olives and liquid.
Heat through.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix eggs, salt and pepper, bread crumbs and ground beef. Shape into bite-size meatballs. Bake in oven or brown in skillet until done; drain grease. Heat chili sauce and jelly together over low heat until smooth. Add meatballs; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken doritos
directions: Boil chicken in salt water until done.
Cool until able to handle.
Reserve broth.
Debone chicken and cut into cubes.
Set aside.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Score cucumbers lengthwise with tines of fork.
Cut into paper-thin slices to measure 4 cups.

Layer cucumber slices in deep bowl or casserole dish, sprinkle with salt every few layers. Cover the cucumbers with plate or whatever you can find to fit your bowl and weight them down with a heavy object (can of fruit, coffee, etc.).
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Drain cucumbers completely, pressing out remaining liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients: pour over slices.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Drain salad before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into greased 12 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: king ranch rotel chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large saucepan, cook pepper and onion in melted butter until tender. Add soups, Ro-Tel and chicken, stirring until well blended. In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put a layer of torn tortillas, soup mixture and cheese, repeating for 3 layers. Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in blender; add chocolate Cool Whip and stir well.
Serve in little dessert bowls.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture into an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares and serve hot.

title: potatoes
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until soft.
Stir in flour. Add milk and cook, stirring until mixture boils and is thickened. Stir in parsley, salt, pepper and 1 cup cheese.
Combine potatoes, eggs and ham in 3-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over potatoes and eggs; mix.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp wild rice soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine wild rice and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Stir in potato soup.
Add half and half, cheese and green onions.
Simmer until cheese is melted, stirring frequently. Add shrimp; heat gently until shrimp are thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally; do not boil.
Garnish each serving with almonds.
Yields 6 (1 1/3-cups) servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
frozen
broccoli	according to package directions and drain.
Mix
in
a	greased casserole dish with croutons. Pour melted
margarine
on top.	Combine the 2 soups and pour over broccoli mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover for the first 30 minutes.
Uncover for the last 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp.
Add mayonnaise, onion, Tabasco sauce and salt. Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Put vegetables into a container that will fit your refrigerator. Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a pan, heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over vegetables, cover and refrigerate. If you are using a glass container be sure to cool brine before adding to prevent your jar from cracking. Should be ready to eat the next day. Keep pickles refrigerated.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease.
Add ground beef to Italian pasta sauce.
Add some oregano and simmer for 1/2 hour.
While it simmers, boil noodles in boiling salted water about 15 minutes; drain them.
Fill a 9 x 15-inch pan with alternate layers of noodles, cheese, tomato-meat sauce and pepperoni, ending with noodles and sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Combine sugar, water and cinnamon in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat until all liquid evaporates (about 15 minutes).
Spread nuts on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out dough in a 12 x 16-inch rectangle.
Combine egg and Parmesan cheese.
Brush dough with mixture.
Cover dough with pepperoni.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up dough.
Put seam side down on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: yuletide drops
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; then add sour cream.
Stir in flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Then mix in oats, pecans, dates and cherries.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
