Place tuna fish in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish (or spray with Pam).
Blend mushroom soup and milk together.
Add salt.
Pour over tuna fish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips or cracker crumbs over top.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Place ground beef in a plastic container.
Place in glass bowl and microwave at Full power for 4 minutes.
Add sauce, water and seasonings.

title: rice risati
directions: Saute onion lightly in butter.
Add rice and brown.
Combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese, and pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed.
Add cheese and stir lightly.

title: sheila's sausage stuff
directions: Brown the sausage and drain.
Mix the cornbread mix as directed on the package and add the can of cream-style corn.
Add the drained sausage.
Stir to combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan until toothpick comes out clean.
Can be served as a dressing or with salsa or fried eggs.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken pieces. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, melt butter.
Add milk and sugar; mix well.
Microwave on High in this order:
3 minutes, stir; 2 minutes, stir; 3 minutes, stir; 2 1/2 minutes, let stand.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla; mix. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and add other ingredients. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Makes a large pie.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: baked curried chicken and rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together water, undrained tomatoes, rice, apricots, raisins, lemon juice, curry powder, bouillon granules, cinnamon, salt, garlic and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling. Stir in poultry.

title: johnny mozette
directions: Put Crisco in skillet; add onion, 2 stalks chopped celery (if celery is desired), pepper, mushrooms and meat.
Cook and stir until meat is browned.
Add tomato sauce, soup and paste, then chopped olives and salt.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Arrange cooked noodles in
casserole, then meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese and run in oven and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This can be divided into 2 smaller casseroles and frozen until ready to bake.

title: united airlines sweet potato (yam) casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Place in a greased casserole dish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in boiler and bring to boil; let simmer a few seconds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all items together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Ritz crackers for topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweet potatoes until smooth.
Mix butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in nutmeg, salt and evaporated milk.
Re-crimp edge of pie crust to stand 1/2-inch above rim.
Place pie crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake in the center of oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shell

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions slowly, spoon off excess fat.
Add all ingredients except noodles and cheeses.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: italian omelette
directions: Break eggs; add a little water and beat.
Put oil in pan and heat.
Pour eggs into pan.
Let them cook about 3 to 5 minutes at medium heat, then add cheeses, as much as you want, but make sure you can still fold the omelette in half in the pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Remove from pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce (heated up of course).
Makes a great brunch meal.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, using a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or round cake pans.
Split cake into 2 layers after cake is cool.
Mix milk into pudding.
Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese and Cool Whip, then fold in pudding.
Spread on first layer, then top layer. Place drained pineapple on top.
Chill for a couple of hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Simmer margarine, onions and mustard in a
large Dutch oven. Add water and cook 15 minutes. Add bouillon cubes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Put toasted bread cubes in a bowl. Add soup.
Top with cheese. Place under broiler until bubbly.

title: kid's soap balls
directions: Put Ivory Snow in large Mix-n-Stor.
In measuring cup mix water, cologne or almond flavoring, and food coloring.
Stir with wooden spoon and pour over Ivory Snow.
After it is completely mixed, shape into balls or shapes with hands.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Mix all together except nuts and apples.
When cool add nuts and apples.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine water, oleo and cocoa; bring to a boil and cool.
Mix together flour, sugar and salt and add to first mixture.
Mix together sour cream and soda; add to first mixture with eggs and mix.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar with hot water. Mix in strawberry Jell-O and Kool-Aid. Add pineapple juice and chill.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Mix the jello and boiling water and then add the cranberries. Stir well.
Add pineapple and wine to the mixture and let sit. Adding nuts to the top is optional.

title: chocolate express cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, granulated sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Gradually stir in the water.
Continue stirring until well blended (do not overmix).
Pour batter into an 8-inch square pan.

title: fresh apple dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: Beat all until smooth.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: shirley's pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix well; then add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: roll your own manicotti
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain and cut the lasagna strips in half.

title: delicious brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla together until well blended.
Add eggs, beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda in another bowl.
Then gradually add this mixture to sugar mixture; beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips; drop by rounded tablespoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet onto a sheet of aluminum foil.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: italian cookies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix thoroughly adding 1 cup more of flour if needed.
Dough must be spongy, not sticky.
Shape in braids or rings.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with milk, powdered sugar and flavoring (Anisette or lemon).

title: teresa's low-fat spaghetti sauce
directions: In 4-quart pan over medium heat, heat oil, add onions and garlic.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until onions are soft.
Stir in tomato paste, parsley, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato sauce, 1 cup water and bay leaf; increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, partially covered, several hours.
Stir often.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Place in pan.
Cook until cheese melts.
Put layer of Doritos in long pan.
Add chicken breasts.
Pour soup mixture over this. Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread 2
directions: Optional:
One-half cup bran may be substituted for 1 cup flour.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until very thick.
Continue to beat; gradually add brandy and rum.
Chill. Transfer to punch bowl and gradually stir in the cream and 3 to 4 cups of milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Serve in punch cups with grated nutmeg.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan for crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pork chop and long grain wild rice
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Salt pork chops; put on top of rice mixture. Cover with foil.
Cook 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
I substitute chicken instead of pork chops.
This is real good reheated.

title: breadsticks
directions: Cut split hot dog buns lengthwise into three strips.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Brush bun strips with melted butter or margarine.
Stir together Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning. Sprinkle atop strips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until toasted and crisp.
Makes 24.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together onion, bread crumbs, spices, egg and 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Add meat and cheeses; mix well.
Pour mixture into large meat loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add remaining tomato sauce and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Remove crust and spread mayonnaise on both sides of bread. Cut bread into cubes.
Place in a buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs well.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread cubes. Spread cheese on top.
Let stand at least 8 hours in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Layer graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over graham crackers, then another layer of grahams.
Warm icing to pouring stage.
Pour over top of graham crackers.
Cool until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese in a medium mixing bowl until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in each paper lined muffin cup. Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafer, filling cups full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Leave in muffin pans and refrigerate overnight. To serve, remove paper liners, if desired, and top with a small amount of pie filling.
Makes 12.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Sift flour 5 times.
Cream butter and shortening well and add sugar gradually.
Add flour, small portions at a time alternately with milk and eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add lemon extract; turn into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Put in a cold oven.
Light oven and set at 325°; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash the sweet potatoes with electric mixer.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, 1/3 cup butter and milk to the potato mix.
Put in greased casserole dish. Combine brown sugar, chopped nuts, flour and 1/3 cup butter. Crumble mixture on top of the potatoes.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients soak overnight.
Rinse well in cold water and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients to zucchini-onion mixture and mix all together.
Cook, stirring, for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Yield:
9 pints.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup and broth.
Add vegetables and cooked chicken.
Mix and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk. Add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. In 3-quart casserole, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix until casserole is full. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs thoroughly with 2/3 cup sugar, dash of salt, dark corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: kristin's mussels
directions: Clean and discard open or broken mussels.
In a large pot, fry garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add clam juice.
Bring to boil.
Add mussels, parsley, basil and butter.
Stir.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in warm water.
Cream shortening and powdered sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and roll into balls.
Dip into sugar and flatten with fork.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: eclairs
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk until mixture thickens.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers.
Cover with half the pudding, another layer of graham crackers.
Add remainder of pudding and another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate icing or another flavor.
You should have 3 layers of crackers and 2 of pudding.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Bring water to boil; add white rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
In large saucepan, bring to boil milk, margarine and onion.
Add broccoli; boil for 5 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam leaves in water for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from boiler and place on wax paper or towel. In a skillet, fry sausage and drain. Boil rice per package directions. (Any rice will work as long as you have 2 to 3 cups cooked.) Mix rice and sausage. Spoon some of mixture into each cabbage leaf and roll leaf, tucking in sides as you roll. Place in casserole dish. Pour tomato sauce over cabbage rolls and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lillian's chocolate lush
directions: Mix together the flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: *May use 12 ounces almond bark instead of these ingredients.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted; add extract.
Blend well; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl; blend well with mixer until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; spread with chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: carr's fork gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together (add enough self-rising flour to make stiff dough).
Bake at 350°.

title: ants on the log
directions: Cut celery into 2-inch lengths.
Stuff with peanut butter. Top each with 2 or 3 raisins.
Arrange on serving plate.
Yields 10 servings.

title: bun steads
directions: Combine cheese, tuna, mayo, eggs, green pepper, onion, olives, relish and mustard.
Divide equally into split buns.
Wrap in foil and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil vinegar.
Add ingredients in glass jar.
Let stand for 10 days.

title: chicken creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and peppers in margarine.
Gradually add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on stove for 1 to 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
If too thin, add a cornstarch mixture to thicken.
If too thick, add more broth.
Serve over rice.

title: mulled cider
directions: Bake orange studded with cloves at 450° for 30 minutes.
Put all of ingredients and orange in crock-pot and simmer 3 to 4 hours (at least).

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix
jello
according to package directions.
Add sliced bananas
and
pineapple.
Add marshmallows and chill until set. After set, top with Cool Whip.

title: baked peaches
directions: Lay peach halves, cavity side up.
Cover with half of the peach syrup.
Put a dab of butter and a touch of brown sugar in each peach half.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Squeeze the juice of a lemon over all.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bar cookies
directions: Press rolls on cookie sheet.
Spread frosting (dry mix) over rolls, then pour milk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt together margarine and sugar.
Be sure sugar is well melted.
Use a heavy utensil at low temperature and stir constantly.
Add egg, cook until thick.
Add dates (dates will dissolve in hot mixture).
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla. Form into small balls, stretch into fingers as you roll.
Then roll in coconut.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: dilly meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place mixture in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: Layer banana slices and cake cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Place strawberries over cake and press down gently.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
Frost with whipped topping.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: peach delite
directions: Combine cake mix and butter to crumble mixture.
Press lightly into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange peaches (well drained) in rows on top.
Beat sour cream and egg yolks.
Pour over peaches.
Spread evenly to size of pan.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until set.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pineapple-orange sunshine cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Mix at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool cake in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: savory roast potatoes
directions: About 50 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°.

In a 17 x 11 1/2-inch roasting pan, toss potatoes and onion with olive or salad oil, salt, dried rosemary and pepper until well coated. Roast potatoes 40 to 45 minutes, turning them occasionally, until potatoes are tender and golden.
Makes 6 accompaniment servings.

title: blitz torte
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten egg yolks, vanilla, milk and sifted dry ingredients.
Spread mixture into two greased pans.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; add remaining sugar gradually and beat until eggs hold a sharp peak. Spread over unbaked batter in both pans.
Sprinkle with walnuts or almonds, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Cool and spread custard filling between layers. Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: walnut cheddar ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: brown stone cake
directions: Dissolve the chocolate in hot water; cool.
Let butter and margarine get real soft.
Cream it with sugar.
Add eggs, beating and scraping bowl all the time.
Add cooled chocolate and water. Then add flour with soda sifted in it alternately with buttermilk. Will be real fluffy.
Will make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: boiled custard
directions: Cook in double boiler 1 hour.
Then add flour; cook 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add raisins or walnuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat with a spoon until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan (8 x 8-inches).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sorry cookies(sorry there ain't no more)
directions: Mix biscuit mix and brown sugar.
Beat eggs, one at a time, into mix.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well (mix will be dry). Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Put drained pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Put on cheese.
Mix flour and sugar and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Put on crushed crackers.
Pour on the melted margarine.
Serve with meats.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients into pan.
Boil, without stirring, until candy forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add a few drops of vanilla.
Set aside to cool, then pour into a greased platter and beat with a fork until creamy.
Mark into squares immediately.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Stir together marinade.
Place London broil in marinade and cover.
Refrigerate overnight; turn meat at least once.
Broil on grill to desired doneness.

title: zucchini or squash cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, oil and zucchini, then add dry ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Very moist.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into pie shell.
Cover and cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: orange, cool whip salad
directions: Let Cool Whip soften, then sprinkle jello powder on top.
Fold together. Add pineapple with the juice and the drained oranges. Add the cottage cheese.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until golden brown. Serves 1.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in soda, cream of tartar, flour and butterscotch morsels.
Bake 8-10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cheesecake
directions: Pour mixture in pan and pack bottom and sides (to hold crumbs on side, grease with soft butter or oleo to hold them there).

title: jumbles
directions: Combine softened margarine and egg.
In a separate bowl, blend together flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into margarine mixture; mix.
Turn out onto floured board and knead lightly a few times until dough forms a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill 1 hour.

title: aunt margaret's nut roll
directions: Crumble yeast in 1/2 cup warm milk.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar. Set aside in a warm place to rise, about 1/2 hour.
Sift flour. Mix in yeast, milk and sugar mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients, margarine, egg yolks and enough warm milk to make a soft dough that doesn't stick.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir molasses, sugar, salt, and spices together.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute
green
peppers in oven dish. Combine beef, peppers,
chili powder, soup, salsa, water and corn.
Bake in 400° oven
until
heated.
Mix corn bread by package directions.
Pour on top of mixture.
Bake according to package or until done.

title: refrigerated sheet cake
directions: Melt the butter or margarine and mix with the graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the graham cracker crumbs.
Put in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan (muffin pan of 12 may be used). Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Add buttermilk. Stir in eggs. Add oil or shortening. Pour batter into greased pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: double chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in bowl; set aside.

Melt margarine in large heavy pot; add milk and vanilla. Stir well, then add sugar mixture. With large metal spoon, stir to bottom of pot and blend all ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes. Continue to stir often to keep from scorching. After 6 minutes, turn off heat; do not remove from unit.
Add morsels, stirring until they are melted; add marshmallow cream and stir until it is melted and well blended with the chocolate. Add nuts; mix well and pour into pans. Let cool and slice.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Heat at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry swirl cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large mixer bowl, blend first 4 ingredients until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into pan.
Reserve 1 cup cherry fruit filling for topping. Spoon remaining cherry fruit filling over cake batter.
Gently swirl through batter to marble. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Spread filling over cake. Top with whipped topping.

title: grandma tillery's cucumber pickles
directions: Soak sliced
cucumbers
in cold water to which lime has been added,
for 24 hours.
Drain and soak in clear cold water for 4 hours;
changing
water
every
hour and draining.
Mix sugar, vinegar and a small box of pickling spices.
Bring to a boil; pour
over
cucumbers.
Let
stand overnight.
Boil one hour;
add a few drops of coloring.
Put in jars and seal.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Add the soda to the sour milk and mix.
Add the remaining ingredients into the bowl without mixing, then beat well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In oven, melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and pour into buttered pan.
Bake eggs about 35 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugars thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and flavorings.
Add
oats;
let
stand awhile.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in fruit, nuts or chips.
Drop
by teaspoonful onto ungreased sheet.	Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Blend in nutmeg, salt, pumpkin and water.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and baking soda. Gradually stir into pumpkin mixture and blend well.
Fold in raisins.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt butter and cool to room temperature.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients in order, stirring after each addition.
Use ice cream scoop, 6 scoops per cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together in order listed and refrigerate.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and let stand, for 2 min. Add large cool whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: camper's punch-out
directions: Mix the lemonade, sugar, cranapple juice and pineapple juice together.
Just before serving, add the lemon-lime drink.
Serve over ice cubes or ice ring made with the fruit of your choice.

title: curly noodle chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute the chicken, onion, celery, carrots and garlic in butter and oil for 5 minutes. Stir in the flour, basil, oregano and pepper until blended. Gradually add broth and tomatoes. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Return to a boil. Stir in the pasta. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes or until pasta is tender. Yield: 9 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Dream Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Add blueberries, cherries, etc., on top.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat whole eggs, sugar, corn syrup, maple syrup, margarine and salt.
Add vinegar and vanilla and beat well.
Using a large wooden spoon, stir in oats and pecans.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large pan.
Add ketchup, tomato sauce or paste, mushroom pieces, bay leaf, oregano and salt. Simmer 3 hours.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl.
Blend well. Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with chips and/or cut fresh vegetables.

title: pineapple-cream cheese cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, bake cake mix as directed.
Then cool.
Whip (room temperature) cream cheese.
Add to it the prepared vanilla pudding.
Spread this mixture over top of cake. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread drained pineapple on top of pudding-cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with walnuts.

title: cheese omelette
directions: Beat the eggs very lightly in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the butter.
Melt the butter in a 9-inch skillet or omelette pan, letting it heat until it has a nutty fragrance, but it is not browned.
Pour the egg mixture into the pan; cook over low heat until lightly browned, pulling the mixture from the sides of the pan with a fork as it cooks.
Turn and brown lightly on the other side.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic powder.
Pour off grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Boil noodles for 10 minutes, drain and rinse with cold water until noodles can be handled.
Arrange in a baking dish a layer of noodles, layer of meat sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with ripe olives (optional).
Bake in oven for one hour at 350°.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Brown meat slowly on all sides in hot Wesson oil.
Remove meat and lower heat.
Add garlic and next 8 seasonings.
Simmer about 5 minutes, being careful not to burn.
Return meat.
Mix tomato paste with water and pour over meat.
Bring to a full boil. Lower heat and cover loosely.
Simmer slowly about 2 to 3 hours, turning meat occasionally.
When meat is tender, cook noodles and drain.
Slice the roast and arrange with noodles.
Cover with the sauce.
Sprinkle with the cheese and chives.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: In
bowl
combine
strawberries,
eggs
and
oil.
In another bowl combine flour, sugars, nuts and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach dip in french bread
directions: For Dip:
In large mixer bowl combine the drained spinach, cream cheese, milk, minced garlic, shredded lemon peel, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and hot pepper sauce.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until combined. Stir in sliced green onion; cover and chill mixture until serving time.

title: microwave coated fish(low-fat)
directions: Thaw fish.
Turn under thin edges in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch low wattage oven). Brush fish with buttermilk.
In a small bowl, cook margarine 30 seconds or until melted. Stir in stuffing mix, salt and pepper. Spoon stuffing over fish.
Cook fish, uncovered, 4 to 7 minutes (7 to 9 for Low) or until fish flakes easily.
Give dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a glass bowl, mix sugar, peanuts and syrup.
Stir.
Put in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Put in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add soda; stir well but hurry.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream orange juice and margarine. In a separate bowl mix pecans, vanilla wafers, 1 box powdered sugar and coconut. Slowly add to orange juice mixture. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Form into balls, roll in remaining sugar and refrigerate.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with your favorite dipables.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break head of cauliflower into small pieces in bottom of bowl. Break lettuce into bite-sized pieces and put over cauliflower. Add chopped onions and bacon.
Sprinkle sugar over bacon.
Add layer of cheese, top with mayonnaise.
Spread to seal.
Chill. Toss before serving.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Arrange fillets in one layer in greased shallow pan.
Pour undiluted soup evenly over fillets. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain water from broccoli. Cook rice. (I cook the rice in 2 cups water; bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.) Drain the water from the rice if necessary. Saute the onion in butter in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add all ingredients to the onions. Cook until cheese is bubbly on top. (I like to cook mine at 300° for about 20 to 30 minutes.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soups and potatoes.
Fold mixture into greased baking dish.
Spread with softened Cheese-Whiz.
Top with sour cream. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top, if desired.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for approximately 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in sealed container.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons to cup of hot water (add more to taste).

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: In large bowl combine all the vegetables.
In a medium saucepan, bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil for two minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over ingredients; stir gently.
Cover and chill overnight.
Stir again; drain before serving.
Yield:
12 to 18 servings.
This makes a nice salad for potluck suppers.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in persimmon pulp and set aside.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Cream together margarine and sugar until fluffy, then beat in egg.
Stir dry ingredients and persimmon mixture into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together Crisco oil, eggs, sugar, flour, salt and soda. Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in a 3-quart pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Set aside to cool.
Blend in eggs, flour, chocolate chips and nuts.
Turn the mixture into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding, dry, into Cool Whip and set aside.
In a large bowl, place 3 ingredients: pineapple with juice, pecans and marshmallows.
Stir in Cool Whip mix and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Make a day ahead to allow flavors to blend.
Chill well.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sauce for baked ham
directions: Put jelly in glass bowl in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mustard.
Heat until hot.
Serve hot with sliced, baked ham.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Mix together cream-style corn, milk, chopped onion and green pepper.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Beat whites until stiff. Add seasoned bread crumbs to mixture until it thickens.
Add butter (3 to 4 Tbsp.) and add yolk.
Mix together well.
Fold in egg whites.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° or 350° until top is brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cream of tartar and water.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add crackers and boil 2 minutes.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake as usual.

title: red radish salad
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice, and sour cream in a medium bowl. Add radishes, apple, and cucumber, toss to coat completely.
Add in salt, pepper, and dill.
Toss.
Chill and serve.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef in butter until crumbly. Add salt, sugar, pepper, garlic and tomato sauce. Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Cook noodles; drain. Chop green onions (use tops, too) and mix with sour cream and cream cheese. After meat sauce has cooled, grease 2-quart casserole and alternate layers: first, noodles; second, cheese mixture; third, meat sauce. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: veal scalloppine with cheese
directions: Pound very thin veal cutlets thinner between 2 pieces of wax paper with flat side of mallet or cleaver.
Beat egg with salt and pepper.
Dip cutlets in egg, then in bread or cracker crumbs. Saute slowly in butter until delicate brown.
Arrange in shallow baking dish; cover with thin layer of cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until cheese is melted.
This should be served right away before cheese hardens.
Serves 4.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Soften butter and ice cream and mix together all ingredients. Store in freezer.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, salt and margarine; blend well.
Press into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts over partially baked crust.
In small saucepan, combine corn syrup, margarine, water and butterscotch chips; boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour cooked mixture over nuts.
Return to oven and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: green chile
directions: Quantities do not have to be exact!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs until smooth.
Add milk and stir well.
Cook (boil) until thick.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour in pie shell.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl combine first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: white icing
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Cook until clear (do not stir) and full of little white bubbles.
Beat egg whites until in peaks, then pour syrup slowly, beating until it holds its shape.
Great for icing of coconut cake.
